oss's%20dumb%20jokes%20are%20funny%20can%20lead%20to%20emotional%20exhaustion%20and%20lower%20job%20satisfaction%2C%20academics%20found%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221969%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Businessman%20Talking%20to%20Bored%20Staff%20in%20Meeting.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e9a7e96080194819fd6e45%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221477%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELaughing%20at%20your%20boss's%20terrible%20jokes%20is%20a%20corporate%20rite%20of%20passage%2C%20but%20it%20isn't%20good%20for%20you.%3Cp%3ETim%20Garcha%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EBosses%20who%20make%20too%20many%20jokes%20can%20actually%20harm%20employee%20wellbeing%2C%20a%20new%20study%20found.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20study%2C%20from%20academics%20at%20three%20elite%20universities%2C%20looked%20at%20the%20impacts%20of%20fake%20positive%20reactions%20to%20jokes%20by%20employees.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20study%20suggests%20that%20bosses%20need%20to%20be%20thoughtful%20about%20how%20they%20express%20humor.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFunny%20bosses%20can%20ease%20up%20a%20serious%20meeting%20or%20lighten%20the%20mood%2C%20but%20a%20new%20study%20has%20found%20that%20cracking%20too%20many%20jokes%20could%20actually%20harm%20employee%20wellbeing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%2C%20recently%20published%20in%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.aom.org%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.5465%2Famj.2022.0195%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%20Academy%20of%20Management%20Journal%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20looks%20at%20how%C2%A0%26quot%3Bleader%20humor%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20when%20someone%20in%20a%20leadership%20position%20expresses%20humor%20%E2%80%94%20puts%20pressure%20on%20subordinates%20to%20engage%20in%20%26quot%3Bsurface%20acting%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20includes%20faking%20or%20exaggerating%20positive%20emotional%20reactions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20includes%20a%20field%20experiment%2C%20laboratory%20experiment%2C%20and%20a%20multi-wave%20field%20study%20and%20was%20authored%20by%20Randall%20Peterson%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20organizational%20behavior%20at%20London%20Business%20School%2C%20Xiaoran%20Hu%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20of%20management%20at%20the%20London%20School%20of%20Economics%2C%20and%20Michael%20Parke%20and%20Grace%20Simon%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20found%20that%20bosses%20who%20make%20too%20many%20jokes%20actually%20increase%20the%20amount%20of%20surface%20acting%20employees%20do%2C%20which%20can%20then%20lead%20to%20emotional%20exhaustion%20or%20burnout%2C%20and%20lower%20levels%20of%20job%20satisfaction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20the%20boss%20tells%20a%20joke%20that%20is%20not%20hilarious%2C%20the%20employee%20has%20to%20decide%20whether%20to%20fake%20laugh%20or%20not%2C%26quot%3B%20Peterson%20told%20Business%20Insider%20via%20email.%20%26quot%3BThat%20decision%20takes%20energy%2C%20no%20matter%20the%20decision.%20If%20they%20fake%20laugh%2C%20that%20is%20additional%20emotional%20labor%20that%20takes%20energy%20away%20from%20work.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20of%20the%20studies%2C%20212%20participants%20from%20a%20behavioral%20lab%20subject%20pool%20at%20a%20business%20school%20in%20the%20northeastern%20United%20States%20took%20part%20in%20what%20they%20were%20told%20was%20an%20hour-long%20focus%20group%20at%20the%20university's%20bookstore%20in%20groups%20of%20three%20to%20five%20people.%C2%A0They%20would%20complete%20a%20survey%20after.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20participants%20would%20enter%20a%20breakout%20room%20and%20would%20be%20greeted%20by%20a%20focus%20group%20leader%20who%20would%20introduce%20himself%20as%20the%20vice%20president%20of%20sales%20at%20the%20university%20bookstore.%20They%20were%20really%20professional%20actors%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2050%20and%2060.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20two%20different%20versions%20of%20the%20task%3A%20one%20in%20which%20there%20was%20a%20high%20power%20distance%20between%20participants%20and%20leaders%20and%20another%20where%20there%20was%20a%20low%20power%20distance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20even%20instructed%20focus%20group%20leaders%20to%20present%20themselves%20in%20two%20different%20ways.%20One%20was%20instructed%20to%20wear%20formal%20business%20attire%2C%20including%20a%20navy%20blue%20suit%20and%20a%20tie%2C%20and%20to%20introduce%20himself%20as%20%26quot%3BMr%20%5BSurname.%5D%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20participants%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Bleading%20the%20session%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20they%20should%20speak%20with%20him%20as%20if%20he%20were%20a%20%26quot%3Bformal%20representative%26quot%3B%20from%20the%20bookstore.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20wore%20business%20casual%20attire%2C%20such%20as%20a%20navy%20blue%20polo%20shirt%2C%20and%20introduced%20himself%20with%20his%20first%20name.%20He%20told%20participants%20that%20%26quot%3Bwe're%20all%20equals%20here%26quot%3B%20and%20to%20talk%20to%20him%20as%20if%20he%20were%20a%20%26quot%3Bfriend.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20instructed%20some%20leaders%20to%20make%20jokes%20like%20puns%20and%20others%20to%20make%20no%20jokes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20found%20that%20the%20leaders%20who%20frequently%20made%20jokes%20increased%20surface%20acting%20in%20followers%2C%20which%20subsequently%20resulted%20in%20poor%20well-being%20outcomes%2C%20including%20emotional%20exhaustion.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20negative%20outcomes%20were%20more%20pronounced%20when%20there%20was%20a%20bigger%20power%20gap%20between%20the%20leader%20and%20follower.%20Subordinates%20felt%20more%20pressure%20to%20fake%20emotions%20when%20there%20was%20a%20larger%20gap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20reason%20followers%20feel%20this%20pressure%20is%20because%20displaying%20the%20correct%20emotion%20might%20be%20instrumental%20to%20their%20personal%20goals%20and%20progression.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20when%20followers%20perceive%20a%20leader%20as%20genuinely%20funny%2C%20frequent%20leader%20humor%20expression%20heightens%20positive%20display%20expectations%20that%20drive%20surface%20acting%20and%20aggravate%20well-being%2C%20especially%20for%20followers%20with%20higher%20power%20distance%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20authors%20wrote.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20surface%20acting%20can%20trigger%20a%20cycle%20of%20negative%20well-being%20outcomes%20for%20employees%2C%20per%20the%20study.%20Funny%20leaders%20tend%20to%20joke%20more%2C%20and%20if%20they're%20receiving%20a%20positive%20reaction%2C%20whether%20that%20be%20surface%20acting%20or%20genuine%20amusement%2C%20it%20could%20encourage%20them%20to%20tell%20even%20more%20jokes%2C%20causing%20more%20surface%20acting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20this%20doesn't%20mean%20the%20end%20of%20bosses%20making%20jokes%20in%20the%20office.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20study%20finds%20that%20%26quot%3Bfewer%2C%20higher-reward%20attempts%26quot%3B%20at%20quality%20humor%20actually%20have%20a%20positive%20outcome%20on%20employee%20wellbeing%20as%20opposed%20to%20making%20too%20many%20jokes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20leaders%20are%20more%20thoughtful%20about%20their%20humor%2C%20it%20actually%20alleviates%20the%20pressure%20of%20surface%20acting.%20Peterson%20advises%20leaders%20to%20use%20humor%20%26quot%3Bsparingly%26quot%3B%20instead.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20they%20say%20in%20the%20US%20Army%3A%20Remember%20when%20in%20a%20leadership%20role%2C%20you%20are%20not%20as%20funny%20as%20you%20think%20you%20are.%20People%20laugh%20because%20you%20are%20the%20boss%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMostly%2C%20control%20how%20much%20humor%20you%20use.%20A%20little%20humor%20goes%20a%20long%20way%20because%20it%20signals%20your%20approval%20of%20relief%20from%20being%20serious%20all%20of%20the%20time.%20Research%20strongly%20supports%20the%20notion%20that%20laughing%20a%20little%20bit%20makes%20us%20more%20productive%20in%20our%20work.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20you%20can%20have%20too%20much%20of%20a%20good%20thing!%20More%20is%20not%20always%20better.%20Or%20think%20of%20humor%20like%20marmite%20%E2%80%94%20a%20little%20goes%20a%20long%20way%2C%20and%20not%20everyone%20likes%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaughing-at-your-boss-dumb-jokes-can-lower-job-satisfaction-study-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709895939000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e9a7fe90413ab8e1da246a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaughing-at-your-boss-dumb-jokes-can-lower-job-satisfaction-study-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Bosses%20who%20make%20too%20many%20jokes%20may%20unintentionally%20pressure%20employees%20to%20pretend%20to%20laugh%20or%20have%20a%20positive%20reaction%2C%20a%20new%20study%20found.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sbhaimiya%40insider.com%20(Sawdah%20Bhaimiya)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaughing-at-your-boss-dumb-jokes-can-lower-job-satisfaction-study-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I'm%20a%20parent%20and%20ex-teacher.%20Teaching%20taught%20me%20how%20to%20do%20gentle%20parenting%20effectively%20%E2%80%94%20and%20why%20most%20people%20do%20it%20wrong.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221944%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mother%20hugging%20and%20comforting%20son.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e7771d90413ab8e1d96b31%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221458%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMany%20people%20misunderstand%20what%20gentle%20parenting%20means.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMore%20parents%20are%20employing%20the%20method%20of%20gentle%20parenting%2C%20but%20many%20misunderstand%20it.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20doesn't%20mean%20you%20allow%20your%20child%20to%20do%20whatever%20they%20want%20and%20never%20discipline%20them.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI%20learned%20a%20lot%20about%20parenting%20when%20I%20was%20a%20teacher.%20Here's%20what%20gentle%20parenting%20actually%20means.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EGentle%20parenting%20is%20a%20clear%20trend%2C%20perhaps%20especially%20among%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-parents-overwhelmed-advice-doubting-their-instincts-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emillennial%20and%20Gen%20Z%20parents%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20stems%20from%20a%20deep%20desire%20to%20respect%20children%20and%20their%20emotions%20with%20the%20hope%20it%20will%20have%20positive%20long-term%20effects%20on%20their%20mental%20health.%20As%20a%20mother%20and%20a%20former%20teacher%2C%20one%20thing%20I've%20noticed%20as%20this%20type%20of%20parenting%20has%20taken%20hold%20is%20that%20there's%20a%20big%20misconception%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20misconception%2C%20held%20by%20both%20gentle%20parents%20themselves%20and%20critics%20of%20it%2C%20is%20this%3A%20that%20there's%20little%20to%20no%20discipline%20involved%20and%20that%2C%20instead%2C%20it's%20all%20about%20staying%20calm%20and%20generally%20accepting%20whatever%20the%20child%20is%20choosing%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20seen%20this%20misunderstood%20version%20of%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-gentle-parenting-and-how-to-follow-it-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egentle%20parenting%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20in%20action%20many%20times.%20One%20that%20stands%20out%20was%20when%20my%20family%20attended%20a%20holiday%20event%20a%20couple%20was%20hosting.%20We%20were%20gathered%20in%20a%20circle%20as%20the%20mother%20began%20with%20a%20reading.%20The%20couple's%20toddler%2C%20instead%20of%20sitting%20in%20his%20chair%2C%20started%20running%20around%20inside%20the%20circle%20and%20being%20generally%20wild.%20The%20father%20was%20standing%20toward%20the%20back%20of%20the%20room%2C%20watching%20his%20wife%20attempt%20to%20both%20lead%20the%20activity%20and%20intermittently%20ask%20the%20child%20%E2%80%94%20%3Cem%3Ecalmly%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20of%20course%20%E2%80%94%20to%20stop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20didn't%20stop%2C%20and%20that%20was%20that.%20Everyone%20in%20attendance%20seemed%20both%20confused%20and%20annoyed%20as%20they%20tried%20to%20pay%20attention%20while%20the%20toddler%20continued%20his%20disruptive%20antics.%20I%20was%20annoyed%20as%20well%2C%20though%20I%20could%20also%20clearly%20see%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faccept-big-feelings-little-kids-normalize-same-for-parents-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egood%20intentions%20of%20the%20parents%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20not%20a%20time%20or%20place%20for%20this%20kind%20of%20behavior%20from%20a%20two-year-old%2C%20however%20normal%20it%20was%20for%20his%20age.%20The%20father%20could%20have%20easily%20helped%20the%20child%20to%20take%20his%20seat%2C%20and%20if%20he%20still%20wouldn't%20sit%20still%2C%20could%20kindly%20have%20removed%20him%20from%20the%20room%20rather%20than%20accepting%20him%20not%20listening.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENuanced%20parenting%20is%20parenting%20between%20extremes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20conception%20of%20gentle%20parenting%20isn't%20working%20%E2%80%94%20for%20parents%20or%20for%20anyone%20else.%20But%20it's%20no%20surprise%20that%20it%20exists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20recently%20watched%20an%20Instagram%20reel%20naming%20the%20various%20%26quot%3Boptions%26quot%3B%20modern%20parents%20feel%20overwhelmed%20by.%20At%20one%20point%2C%20it%20said%2C%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fparenting%2Fauthoritative-parenting%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYou%20should%20discipline%3C%2Fa%3E%20%2F%20you%20should%20do%20gentle%20parenting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20captures%20it.%20We%20seem%20to%20hold%20two%20possibilities%20in%20our%20minds%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20raising%20and%20being%20in%20charge%20of%20children%3A%20either%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fparenting%2Fauthoritarian-parenting%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eversion%20that's%20authoritarian%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20adults%20speak%20firmly%20and%20children%20immediately%20fall%20in%20line%2C%20and%20one%20that's%20the%20complete%20opposite%2C%20where%20kids%20do%20whatever%20they%20want%20and%20we're%20nice%20to%20them%20and%20hope%20for%20the%20best.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20we're%20talking%20about%20parenting%20or%20any%20other%20topic%2C%20it's%20easy%20to%20see%20something%20as%20this%20or%20that%2C%20and%20swing%20from%20one%20extreme%20to%20the%20other.%20It's%20much%20more%20difficult%20to%20find%20a%20nuanced%20middle%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETeaching%20taught%20me%20to%20find%20the%20nuance%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20experiences%20in%20the%20classroom%20have%20helped%20me%20parent%20in%20this%20%26quot%3Bmiddle%20ground%26quot%3B%20type%20of%20way.%20Good%20teachers%20are%20kind%20and%20respectful%20with%20children%2C%20and%20they%20also%20hold%20them%20to%20behavior%20expectations.%20It's%20an%20art%2C%20to%20be%20sure%2C%20but%20it's%20absolutely%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20a%20few%20things%20I%20learned%20from%20teaching%20that%20I've%20applied%20as%20a%20parent%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstopped-gentle-parenting-scripts-better-relationship-with-kids-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebelieves%20in%20gentle%20parenting%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EMake%20expectations%20explicit%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20excellent%20teacher%20knows%20the%20importance%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fsex-relationships%2Feffective-communication%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esetting%20expectations%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20behavior%20upfront%2C%20even%20with%20small%20things%2C%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20how%20I%20want%20you%20to%20turn%20in%20your%20papers.%26quot%3B%20It%20isn't%20fair%20to%20expect%20something%20of%20someone%20else%20%E2%80%94%20a%20child%20or%20otherwise%20%E2%80%94%20unless%20you've%20communicated%20said%20expectations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20crucial%20part%20of%20effective%20discipline%2C%20the%20conveying%20(and%20modeling%20and%20practicing)%20of%20appropriate%20behavior%2C%20and%20one%20that%20often%20is%20missed.%20We%20can't%20just%20expect%20kids%20to%20know%20what%20we%20want%20to%20see%20from%20them%20%E2%80%94%20we%20need%20to%20know%20exactly%20what%20we%20want%20and%20then%20clearly%20let%20them%20know%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EEvery%20errant%20behavior%20doesn't%20need%20a%20punishment%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20should%20be%20addressed%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ERegarding%20misbehavior%2C%20there%20is%20a%20vast%20space%20between%20doing%20nothing%20and%20delivering%20a%20harsh%20punishment.%20When%20kids%20don't%20measure%20up%2C%20we%20do%20need%20to%20let%20them%20know%2C%20but%20it%20also%20doesn't%20need%20to%20be%20a%20big%20deal.%20This%20is%20often%20a%20simple%20conversation%20that%20reinforces%20the%20expectation.%20Saying%20something%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20remember%2C%20you%20need%20to%20_____%2C%26quot%3B%20works%20well.%20Telling%20them%20the%20%26quot%3Bwhy%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20expectations%20helps%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20teaching%2C%20if%20expectations%20have%20been%20made%20clear%20and%20have%20been%20reinforced%2C%20that's%20often%20enough%20for%20most%20kids.%20In%20parenting%2C%20not%20so%20much.%20But%20again%20%E2%80%94%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20we%20need%20to%20be%20harsh%3B%20it%20just%20means%20we%20need%20to%20move%20on%20to%20an%20intervention%20of%20some%20kind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20very%20young%20children%2C%20this%20often%20looks%20like%20calm%20but%20confident%20physical%20intervention%2C%20like%20holding%20their%20body%20(if%20they're%20hitting%2C%20for%20example)%20or%20removing%20them%20from%20a%20situation.%20For%20older%20ones%2C%20logical%20consequences%20work%20best.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgentle-parenting-tiktok-creators-controversy-explained-interviews-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EParents%20have%20to%20use%20their%20best%20judgment%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20moment%2C%20but%20overall%2C%20follow-through%20of%20some%20kind%20is%20necessary%20if%20you've%20set%20expectations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20strong%20relationship%20is%20the%20most%20important%20foundation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20meaning%20of%20the%20word%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-discipline-kids-top-psychologist-2017-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ediscipline%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20close%20to%20%26quot%3Bteach.%26quot%3B%20Establishing%20a%20warm%2C%20genuine%20relationship%20is%20the%20foundation%20of%20good%20teaching%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20of%20good%20parenting.%20It's%20our%20connections%20with%20children%20that%20give%20us%20the%20power%20to%20influence%2C%20teach%2C%20and%20yes%2C%20to%20%3Cem%3Ediscipline%3C%2Fem%3E%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGood%20relationships%20don't%2C%20however%2C%20ensure%20that%20there%20won't%20be%20any%20unpleasant%20moments.%20A%20strong%20relationship%20with%20a%20child%20means%20valuing%20them%20for%20who%20they%20are%2C%20not%20for%20their%20behavior.%20Out%20of%20that%20place%2C%20we%20can%20discipline%20effectively%2C%20which%20will%20sometimes%20mean%20having%20uncomfortable%20interactions.%20However%2C%20good%20relationships%20can%20withstand%20the%20tension%20and%20conflict