n-law's%20place%20nearby%2C%20and%20she%20said%20they%20came%20down%20to%20the%20community%20every%20three%20days%20to%20help%20in%20the%20recovery%20process.%20There%20was%20no%20power%20or%20water%2C%20and%20she%20felt%20her%20childhood%20survival%20skills%20coming%20back%20into%20play.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20had%20already%20said%20goodbye%20to%20some%20of%20those%20sentimental%20things%20per%20se%2C%20but%20I%20felt%20a%20really%20heavy%20heart%20for%20some%20of%20those%20people%20here%20who%20weren't%20able%20to%20do%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Pelton%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20connection%20from%20Minnesota%20who%20lives%20nearby%20in%20Florida%20heard%20about%20their%20story%20and%20offered%20to%20let%20them%20stay%20at%20the%20house%20for%20as%20long%20as%20needed.%20Their%20Minnesota%20home%20still%20hadn't%20sold%2C%20so%20they%20stayed%20at%20the%20home%20for%20two%20months%20and%20used%20an%20Airbnb%20voucher%20for%20hurricane%20survivors.%20She%20also%20received%20%24700%20from%20FEMA%20for%20initial%20needs.%20In%20between%20volunteering%2C%20she%20said%20she%20kept%20up%20with%20yoga.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20the%20landlord%20allowed%20them%20to%20purchase%20their%20rental%20home%20that%20was%20damaged%20in%20the%20storm%2C%20and%20within%20a%20few%20months%2C%20they%20started%20to%20repair%20it%20and%20get%20their%20business%20back%20up%20and%20running.%20She%20donated%20much%20of%20her%20business%20merchandise%20to%20assist%20those%20who%20lost%20more%20belongings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMinnesota%20vs.%20Florida%3A%20Pros%20and%20cons%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPelton%20estimated%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcost-of-living-florida-cities-prices-housing-medical-energy-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eliving%20costs%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20cheaper%20in%20Florida%2C%20although%20she%20said%20wages%20tend%20to%20be%20lower.%20She%20said%20utilities%20are%20about%20the%20same%2C%20as%20she%20uses%20more%20AC%20but%20less%20heat%20in%20Florida.%20Gas%20prices%20are%20slightly%20higher%20in%20Florida%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgasprices.aaa.com%2F%3Fstate%3DFL%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%243.31%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20gallon%2C%20compared%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgasprices.aaa.com%2F%3Fstate%3DMN%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%243.17%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Minnesota.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20just%20a%20personal%20preference%3A%20Do%20you%20want%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20cold%20for%20a%20few%20months%2C%20or%20do%20you%20want%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20extreme%20heat%20for%20a%20few%20months%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20housing%20prices%20are%20still%20elevated%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-orlando-florida-cheaper-homes-from-miami-california-ny-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFlorida%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20though%20she's%20not%20seeing%20many%20homes%20in%20her%20area%20selling%20as%20the%20housing%20market%20recovers%20from%20Hurricane%20Ian.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoving%20to%20Florida%20was%20%26quot%3Bby%20far%20a%20better%20choice%26quot%3B%20for%20her%20to%20launch%20the%20business%2C%20as%20the%20clientele%20is%20more%20%26quot%3Beclectic%26quot%3B%20and%20interested%20in%20sustainable%20clothing%2C%20Pelton%20said.%20She%20said%20there's%20a%20higher%20demand%20for%20athleisure%20wear%20in%20Florida%2C%20and%20the%20business%20has%20grown%20much%20faster%20than%20she%20believes%20it%20would%20have%20in%20Minnesota.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPelton%20said%20it%20took%20time%20to%20get%20used%20to%20seasonal%20economic%20differences%20in%20Florida%2C%20where%20the%20economy%20booms%20between%20Memorial%20Day%20and%20Labor%20Day%20and%20businesses%20shutter%20in%20the%20winter.%20She%20said%20in%20Minnesota%2C%20the%20slower%20months%20are%20often%20during%20the%20summer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20in%20Florida%2C%20it's%20much%20easier%20to%20eat%20healthy%20with%20readily%20available%20fruit%20and%20vegetables.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20she%20said%20the%20weather%20overall%20is%20more%20pleasant%2C%20especially%20for%20outdoor%20chores%20such%20as%20gardening.%20She%20misses%20Minnesota's%20lakes%2C%20as%20many%20in%20Florida%20are%20not%20suitable%20for%20swimming%20due%20to%20the%20presence%20of%20snakes%20and%20alligators.%20She%20said%20she's%20also%20adjusting%20to%20the%20fishing%20scene%20in%20Florida%2C%20which%20is%20mainly%20saltwater%2C%20compared%20to%20freshwater%20fishing%20in%20Minnesota.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20all%20she's%20been%20through%2C%20Pelton%20thinks%20she'll%20stay%20in%20Florida%20for%20the%20time%20being%20%E2%80%94%20the%20only%20other%20place%20she's%20considering%20is%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20in%20the%20back%20of%20my%20mind%2C%20I'm%20going%20to%20do%20what%20a%20woman%20had%20suggested%20of%20a%20lifetime%20where%20you%20move%20across%20towns%2C%20move%20across%20states%2C%20move%20across%20countries%2C%26quot%3B%20Pelton%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20you%20recently%20moved%20to%20a%20new%20state%20or%20moved%20out%20of%20the%20US%20to%20a%20different%20country%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ansheidlower%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ensheidlower%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-florida-from-minnesota-weather-hurricane-insurance-retirement-expensive-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709895662000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e74b64ce7f1785b2e65ce3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-florida-from-minnesota-weather-hurricane-insurance-retirement-expensive-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20boomer%20and%20her%20husband%20moved%20to%20southwest%20Florida%20from%20Minnesota%20to%20start%20her%20clothing%20business%2C%20though%20she%20lost%20nearly%20everything%20in%20a%20hurricane.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22nsheidlower%40insider.com%20(Noah%20Sheidlower)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-florida-from-minnesota-weather-hurricane-insurance-retirement-expensive-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22We%20were%20so%20lonely%20and%20isolated%20after%20moving%20to%20a%20Colorado%20mountain%20town%20we%20went%20back%20to%20New%20York%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20couple%20stood%20in%20the%20Colorado%20mountains.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65eada7f90413ab8e1da9f4a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJackie%20Branholm%20and%20her%20partner%20love%20hiking%20in%20the%20Colorado%20mountains%2C%20but%20had%20a%20different%20experience%20as%20residents.%3Cp%3EJackie%20Branholm%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EJackie%20Branholm%20and%20her%20husband%20moved%20from%20Brooklyn%20to%20Colorado%20and%20bought%20a%20mountain%20house.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey%20loved%20being%20close%20to%20hiking%20trails%2C%20but%20were%20unprepared%20for%20the%20realities%20of%20mountain%20life.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEndless%20house%20maintenance%2C%20isolation%20from%20friends%20and%20a%20new%20baby%20deepened%20the%20sense%20they'd%20made%20a%20mistake.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Jackie%20Branholm%20about%20moving%20to%20Evergreen%2C%20Colorado.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20moved%20from%20Brooklyn%20to%20Colorado%20in%20May%202019%20with%20my%20now%20husband.%20After%20a%20West%20Coast%20road%20trip%2C%20we%20chose%20Denver%20for%20the%20fun%20city%20vibes%2C%20sunny%20weather%2C%20and%20access%20to%20outdoor%20activities%20like%20hiking%20and%20skiing.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20timing%20felt%20right%20to%20do%20something%20different%20before%20eventually%20settling%20down%20and%20starting%20a%20family.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20husband%20and%20I%20both%20found%20new%20jobs%2C%20and%20they%20paid%20for%20relocation%2C%20which%20helped%20with%20the%20expense%20of%20moving%20across%20the%20country.%20We%20rented%20an%20apartment%20in%20the%20Lower%20Highlands%20neighborhood.%20Living%20in%20Denver%20was%20amazing%3B%20we%20loved%20spending%20time%20with%20friends%20while%20exploring%20the%20city%20and%20mountains%20nearby.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20the%20idea%20of%20mountain%20living.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20working%20from%20home%20for%20over%20a%20year%20with%20our%20new%20dog%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20we%20got%20house%20fever%20and%20itched%20for%20more%20space.%20We%20saved%20toward%20a%20house%20each%20month%20by%20putting%20aside%20money%20from%20our%20paychecks%20and%20my%20husband's%20commission%20earnings.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThough%20we%20hoped%20to%20buy%20in%20Denver%2C%20we%20were%20priced%20out.%20During%20our%20search%2C%20we%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20the%20idea%20of%20living%20in%20the%20mountains%20with%20our%20growing%20family.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20our%20real-estate%20agent%20and%20financial%20advisor%2C%20we%20found%20a%20house%20that%20fit%20our%20budget%20in%20Evergreen%2C%20a%20mountain%20town%2045%20minutes%20from%20Denver.%20The%20house%20was%20built%20in%201937%20and%20would%20need%20some%20TLC.%20The%20housing%20market%20was%20wild%20then%2C%20so%20we%20felt%20pressured%20to%20decide%20quickly%20after%20seeing%20the%20house%20for%20only%2015%20minutes.%20We%20ended%20up%20buying%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cspan%3EOur%20experience%20in%20Colorado%20shifted%20after%20moving%20to%20the%20mountains%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20moving%20into%20our%20home%20in%20May%202021%2C%20our%20experience%20in%20Colorado%20shifted.%20What%20we%20loved%20about%20the%20town%20when%20we%20visited%20on%20the%20weekends%20was%20not%20the%20same%20experience%20as%20a%20resident.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELiving%20and%20owning%20a%20house%20in%20the%20mountains%20required%20more%20maintenance%20than%20expected.%20We%20had%20over%20an%20acre%20of%20land.%20The%20yard%20work%2C%20renovations%2C%20and%20septic%20maintenance%20took%20up%20most%20of%20our%20free%20time%20on%20weekends.%20Plus%2C%20there%20were%20a%20lot%20of%20unforeseen%20costs.%20We%20factored%20some%20renovations%20into%20our%20overall%20costs%20but%20had%20to%20do%20more%20than%20initially%20planned.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20example%2C%20soon%20after%20moving%20in%2C%20I%20noticed%20my%20blonde%20highlights%20and%20some%20of%20our%20laundry%20had%20a%20green%20tint%20due%20to%20our%20hard%20well%20water.%20To%20fix%20this%2C%20we%20installed%20a%20water%20filter%20for%20%245%2C000.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20shag%20carpet%20covering%20the%20floors%20needed%20to%20be%20replaced%2C%20and%20the%20cost%20to%20refinish%20the%20original%20hardwood%20floor%2C%20as%20well%20as%20add%20tile%20to%20the%20entryway%2C%20was%20%2420%2C000.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20I%20got%20pregnant%20with%20my%20son%20six%20months%20into%20owning%20the%20house%2C%20we%20rushed%20to%20finish%20our%20renovation%20projects%20before%20the%20baby%20came.%20The%20time%20that%20we%20would%20have%20spent%20with%20friends%20in%20Denver%20was%20instead%20spent%20doing%20DIY.%20This%20strained%20our%20now%20long-distance%20friendships.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20felt%20isolated%20from%20friends%20and%20far%20from%20amenities%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELiving%20in%20the%20mountains%20wasn't%20easy%20even%20after%20the%20house%20projects%20were%20over.%20Logistically%20and%20physically%2C%20we%20felt%20isolated.%20If%20we%20wanted%20to%20go%20to%20Target%20or%20the%20grocery%20store%2C%20we%20had%20to%20drive%20at%20least%2020%20minutes.%20Though%20living%20on%20the%20side%20of%20a%20mountain%20gave%20us%20beautiful%20views%2C%20carrying%20groceries%20up%20two%20flights%20of%20stairs%20from%20the%20drive%20to%20the%20front%20door%20and%20another%20flight%20to%20the%20kitchen%20was%20a%20daily%20expedition.%20We%20no%20longer%20had%20easy%20access%20to%20our%20Denver%20friends%2C%20bars%2C%20and%20coffee%20shops.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20were%20fewer%20doctor%20and%20veterinarian%20options%2C%20which%20meant%20more%20planning%20and%20time%20spent%20going%20to%20appointments.%20Access%20to%20Denver%20was%20different%20than%20we'd%20expected.%20It%20was%20a%2045-minute%20drive%2C%20and%20we%20couldn't%20get%20an%20Uber%20from%20our%20house.%20The%20unpredictable%20mountain%20weather%20meant%20we%20couldn't%20always%20drive.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20we%20rarely%20saw%20the%20friends%20we'd%20made%20in%20Denver%20and%20lost%20several%20of%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEventually%2C%20this%20took%20a%20toll%20on%20my%20mental%20health.%20The%20isolation%20was%20tough%2C%20especially%20as%20I%20was%20already%20overwhelmed%20with%20the%20unfamiliar%20responsibilities%20of%20owning%20a%20home%20and%20having%20a%20newborn.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThings%20that%20used%20to%20get%20me%20out%20of%20a%20funk%2C%20like%20seeing%20friends%20and%20workout%20classes%2C%20were%20no%20longer%20easily%20accessible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20a%20new%20baby%2C%20we%20wanted%20to%20be%20closer%20to%20family%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELife%20felt%20particularly%20difficult%20because%20we%20were%20far%20from%20family.%20Though%20we%20still%20had%20some%20friends%20in%20Colorado%2C%20the%20closest%20family%20member%20was%20on%20the%20East%20Coast.%20Having%20our%20son%20intensified%20the%20issues%20we%20were%20already%20facing.%20We%20lacked%20the%20support%20system%20we%20could%20get%20living%20closer%20to%20family.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUltimately%2C%20we%20realized%20how%20and%20who%20we%20spent%20our%20time%20with%20was%20more%20important%20than%20where%20we%20lived.%20Even%20though%20we%20loved%20going%20outside%20and%20hiking%2C%20our%20priorities%20changed%20when%20we%20had%20our%20son.%20We%20wanted%20life%20to%20be%20easier.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EConstant%20house%20work%20made%20it%20feel%20like%20we'd%20made%20a%20mistake%20buying%20an%20older%20home%20that%20needed%20repair.%20Before%20selling%2C%20we%20wanted%20to%20ensure%20we%20timed%20the%20sale%20with%20when%20the%20market%20would%20be%20most%20in%20our%20favor.%20Ultimately%2C%20our%20real-estate%20agent%20advised%20us%20to%20sell%20in%20early%20spring%202023%20after%20ski%20season.%20The%20real-estate%20market%20is%20extremely%20competitive%2C%20and%20the%20warmer%20months%20are%20the%20most%20popular%20time%20to%20sell.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAfter%204%20years%20in%20Colorado%20and%202%20years%20of%20isolated%20mountain%20living%2C%20we%20returned%20to%20New%20York%20%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFour%20years%20after%20moving%20to%20Colorado%2C%20we%20returned%20to%20my%20home%20state%20of%20New%20York%20to%20be%20closer%20to%20family.%20Since%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20both%20work%20remotely%2C%20we%20were%20able%20to%20move%20with%20flexibility.%20Fortunately%2C%20we%20recouped%20the%20money%20we%20put%20in%20when%20we%20sold.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThough%20living%20in%20the%20mountains%20was%20beautiful%2C%20we%20preferred%20to%20be%20in%20a%20convenient%20city%20environment%20where%20grocery%20stores%2C%20restaurants%2C%20and%20day%20care%20were%20closer%20to%20us.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20we%20didn't%20mind%20driving%20further%20to%20hike%20and%20do%20activities%20on%20the%20weekends.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBefore%20making%20an%20offer%20on%20our%20next%20home%2C%20we%20did%20an%20inspection%20and%20used%20that%20to%20inform%20our%20purchase.%20From%20the%20outset%2C%20we%20communicated%20clearly%20with%20our%20new%20real-estate%20agent%20that%20we%20wanted%20to%20take%20our%20time%3B%20any%20house%20that%20required%20us%20to%20move%20extremely%20quickly%20wouldn't%20be%20for%20us.%20We%20saw%20our%20current%20house%20three%20times%20before%20making%20an%20offer.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EColorado%20felt%20like%20a%20huge%20mistake%20at%20the%20time%2C%20but%20it%20was%20a%20lesson%20%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20miss%20ski%20season%20and%20my%20few%20close%20friends%20out%20west%2C%20but%20I'm%20more%20content%20than%20I%20ever%20imagined%20with%20our%20living%20situation%20now.%20We%20love%20the%20convenient%20location%20of%20our%20new%20house%20and%20the%20proximity%20to%20family%20and%20friends.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlthough%20we%20don't%20see%20mountains%20outside%20our%20door%2C%20we%20can%20walk%20a%20few%20blocks%20to%20get%20coffee%2C%20and%20we%20have%20a%20nice%20neighborhood%20with%20a%20good%20school%20district%20for%20our%20son%20once%20he%20is%20older.%20Overall%2C%20we%20love%20the%20house%2C%20and%20it's%20much%20less%20maintenance.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20thick%20of%20feeling%20stressed%20about%20our%20life%20in%20Colorado%2C%20I%20often%20felt%20we'd%20made%20a%20huge%20mistake.%20Although%20it%20was%20difficult%2C%20the%20experience%20helped%20us%20make%20a%20thoughtful%20decision%20on%20our%20current%20home%2C%20which%20we%20love.%20Our%20time%20in%20Colorado%20was%20a%20learning%20experience%2C%20and%20I'm%20glad%20it%20was%20only%20temporary.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-to-colorado-mountains-mistake-left-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709895651000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65eae5c26080194819fde236%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-to-colorado-mountains-mistake-left-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Jackie%20Branholm%20moved%20to%20Colorado%20to%20be%20closer%20to%20hiking%20and%20skiing%2C%20but%20living%20in%20the%20mountains%20was%20a%20different%20experience%20than%20weekend%20trips.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Sophie%20Katzman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-to-colorado-mountains-mistake-left-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Despite%20Talk%20of%20Diversity%2C%20Women%20Still%20a%20Minority%20in%20Indian%20Boardrooms%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F08151835%2Fboard-room-unsplash_resize.jpg.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Gender%20parity%20in%20Indian%20boardrooms%20continues%20to%20remain%20elusive%2C%20with%20a%20decline%20in%20the%20number%20of%20women%20occupying%20key%20positions%20in%20public%20sector%20boardrooms%20over%20the%20past%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findustry%2Fnews%2Finternational-women-s-day-public-private-gap-widens-on-women-directors-124030701035_1.html%5C%22%3Edata%20has%20revealed%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20data%20from%20primeinfobase.com%2C%20a%20mere%2019%25%20of%20total%20directorships%20are%20held%20by%20women%20in%20the%20private%20sector%20while%2014.3%25%20in%20the%20public%20sector%20for%20Nifty%20500%20companies%2C%20as%20of%20March%206.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20has%20been%20a%20marginal%20increase%20in%20the%20number%20of%20women%20in%20private%20sector%20directorships%2C%20rising%20from%20759%20in%20March%202023%20to%20799%20in%202024%2C%20the%20public%20sector%20witnessed%20a%20decrease%20from%2085%20to%2084%20directorships%20during%20the%20same%20period.%20Consequently%2C%20the%20public%20sector%E2%80%99s%20share%20of%20directorships%20fell%20from%2014.7%25%20to%2014.3%25%2C%20%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findustry%2Fnews%2Finternational-women-s-day-public-private-gap-widens-on-women-directors-124030701035_1.html%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20marks%20a%20wider%20gender%20gap%20compared%20to%20the%20previous%20year%2C%20with%20women%20facing%20challenges%20in%20heading%20crucial%20board%20committees%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20gender%20disparity%20extends%20to%20board%20committees%2C%20where%20women%20find%20themselves%20in%20the%20minority%2C%20holding%20approximately%2014%25%20of%20positions%20in%20risk%20management%20and%20over%2020%25%20in%20the%20nomination%20and%20remuneration%20committee.%20Meanwhile%20men%20occupy%20around%20eight%20out%20of%2010%20board%20committee%20positions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20a%20large%20number%20of%20board%20rooms%20are%20due%20for%20a%20shuffle%20this%20year%20as%20The%20Companies%20Act%2C%20which%20came%20into%20force%20in%202014%2C%20mandates%20a%2010-year%20term%20for%20independent%20directors.%20This%20means%20as%20companies%20refresh%20their%20boards%20this%20year%2C%20they%20will%20have%20an%20opportunity%20to%20achieve%20at%20least%2030%25%20representation%20of%20women%20in%20boardrooms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithout%20this%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findustry%2Fnews%2Finternational-women-s-day-public-private-gap-widens-on-women-directors-124030701035_1.html%5C%22%3E%20the%20target%20of%2030%25%20gender%20diversity%20in%20the%20boardroom%20will%20only%20be%20met%20by%202058%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20current%20pace%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20might%20see%20an%20uptick%20as%20a%20consequence.%20While%20it%20is%20important%20to%20look%20at%20women%E2%80%99s%20representation%20across%20the%20board%2C%20another%20metric%20would%20be%20to%20look%20at%20women%20in%20the%20workforce.%20This%20indicator%20would%20be%20helpful%20to%20understand%20gender%20diversity%20at%20a%20broader%20level%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20for%20the%20company%2C%20but%20the%20economy%2C%E2%80%9D%20Amit%20Tandon%2C%20founder%20and%20managing%20director%20of%20IiAS%20told%20%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20data%20from%20the%20Centre%20for%20Monitoring%20Indian%20Economy%2C%20only%2011.1%25%20of%20working-age%20Indian%20women%20were%20employed%20or%20seeking%20employment%20as%20of%20February%202024%2C%20compared%20to%20a%2068.1%25%20labor%20force%20participation%20rate%20for%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20data%20from%20Deloitte%20Global%20Boardroom%20Program%E2%80%99s%20Women%20in%20the%20Boardroom%20report%20shows%20that%20only%205.1%25%20of%20the%20CEOs%20in%20the%20400%20listed%20companies%20on%20the%20MSCI%20index%20are%20women.%20This%20figure%20stood%20at%203.4%25%20in%202018%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fjobs%2Fc-suite%2Fcos-talk-up-diversity-but-boards-stay-stubbornly-male-with-needle-barely-moving-in-6-yrs-survey%2Farticleshow%2F108309038.cms%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20400%20companies%20have%20a%20total%20of%20524%20women%20directors.%20This%20includes%20those%20companies%20that%20only%20fulfil%20the%20condition%20of%20having%20one%20woman%20director%2C%20implying%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20just%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fjobs%2Fc-suite%2Fcos-talk-up-diversity-but-boards-stay-stubbornly-male-with-needle-barely-moving-in-6-yrs-survey%2Farticleshow%2F108309038.cms%5C%22%3Ea%20ticking-the-box%20exercise%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COrganisations%20have%20to%20address%20the%20issue%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20pyramid%20by%20including%20equal%20number%20of%20women%20right%20at%20the%20fresher%20level%2C%E2%80%9D%20Wipro%20chief%20financial%20officer%20Aparna%20Iyer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fjobs%2Fc-suite%2Fcos-talk-up-diversity-but-boards-stay-stubbornly-male-with-needle-barely-moving-in-6-yrs-survey%2Farticleshow%2F108309038.cms%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThen%20they%20have%20to%20retain%20the%20women%20through%20their%20toughest%20and%20key%20life%20stages%20such%20as%20maternity%20and%20care%20giving.%20It%20is%20crucial%20then%20that%20organisations%20proactively%20build%20a%20robust%20leadership%20pipeline%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709895624000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F08151835%2Fboard-room-unsplash_resize.jpg.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fdespite-talk-of-diversity-women-still-a-minority-in-indian-boardrooms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22According%20to%20data%20from%20primeinfobase.com%2C%20a%20mere%2019%25%20of%20total%20directorships%20are%20held%20by%20women%20in%20the%20private%20sector%20while%2014.3%25%20in%20the%20public%20sector%20for%20Nifty%20500%20companies%2C%20as%20of%20March%206.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fdespite-talk-of-diversity-women-still-a-minority-in-indian-boardrooms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mortgage%20Interest%20Rates%20Today%2C%20March%208%2C%202024%20%7C%20Rates%20Are%20Down%2