%9Cexceptional%20contributions%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20fields%20of%20the%20humanities%2C%20social%20sciences%20or%20arts%20in%20Europe%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20March%207%2C%20Ghosh%20posted%20on%20social%20media%20that%20it%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdelight%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Chonour%E2%80%9D%20to%20be%20conferred%20the%20award.%20He%20will%20receive%20the%20award%20in%20person%20in%20the%20Netherlands%20in%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20Ghosh%E2%80%99s%20works%20including%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Great%20Derangement%3C%2Fi%3E%20and%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Nutmeg%E2%80%99s%20Curse%3C%2Fi%3E%20dwell%20on%20the%20ongoing%20planetary%20crisis%20and%20are%20interlinked%20with%20the%20impacts%20of%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ERecurring%20themes%20of%20nature%2C%20people%2C%20and%20climate%20change%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENature%2C%20people%2C%20and%20interactions%20between%20both%2C%20have%20been%20major%20themes%20in%20several%20of%20Ghosh%E2%80%99s%20works%20%E2%80%93%20from%20some%20parts%20in%20his%20fictional%20Ibis%20trilogy%20(%3Ci%3ESea%20of%20Poppies%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20%3Ci%3ERiver%20of%20Smoke%3C%2Fi%3E%20and%20%3Ci%3EFlood%20of%20Fire%3C%2Fi%3E)%20to%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Hungry%20Tide%3C%2Fi%3E.%20The%20latter%20%E2%80%93%20published%2020%20years%20ago%20%E2%80%93%20dwells%20on%20the%20story%20of%20a%20marine%20biologist%20in%20search%20of%20the%20rare%20Irrawady%20dolphin%20in%20the%20Sunderbans.%20Set%20against%20the%20backdrop%20of%20climate%20change%20and%20a%20cyclone%20that%20changes%20the%20protagonists%E2%80%99%20lives%2C%20the%20book%20also%20touched%20on%20man-animal%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20of%20Ghosh%E2%80%99s%20books%2C%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Great%20Derangement%3A%20Climate%20Change%20and%20the%20Unthinkable%3C%2Fi%3E%20(2016)%20is%20a%20non-fictional%20work%20that%20touches%20on%20colonialism%20and%20the%20politics%20interlinked%20with%20climate%20change%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20art%20of%20writing%20about%20the%20issue.%20In%20his%20latest%20book%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Nutmeg%E2%80%99s%20Curse%3C%2Fi%3E%20%E2%80%93%20written%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20%E2%80%93%20Ghosh%20explores%20the%20exploitation%20of%20indigenous%20communities%2C%20ownership%20of%20natural%20resources%20and%20their%20use%2C%20along%20with%20climate%20change%20and%20colonialism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%98Imagining%20the%20unthinkable%E2%80%99%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHe%20receives%20the%20prize%20for%20his%20passionate%20contribution%20to%20the%20theme%20%E2%80%98imagining%20the%20unthinkable%E2%80%99%2C%20in%20which%20an%20unprecedented%20global%20crisis%20%E2%80%93%20climate%20change%20%E2%80%93%20takes%20shape%20through%20the%20written%20word%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Praemium%20Erasmianum%20Foundation%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ferasmusprijs.org%2Fen%2Flaureates%2Famitav-ghosh%2F%5C%22%3Epress%20release%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CGhosh%20has%20delved%20deeply%20into%20the%20question%20of%20how%20to%20do%20justice%20to%20this%20existential%20threat%20that%20defies%20our%20imagination.%20His%20work%20offers%20a%20remedy%20by%20making%20an%20uncertain%20future%20palpable%20through%20compelling%20stories%20about%20the%20past.%20He%20also%20wields%20his%20pen%20to%20show%20that%20the%20climate%20crisis%20is%20a%20cultural%20crisis%20that%20results%20from%20a%20dearth%20of%20the%20imagination%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGhosh%20expressed%20his%20%E2%80%9Cdelight%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Chonour%E2%80%9D%20on%20the%20award%20on%20March%207%2C%20via%20a%20post%20on%20the%20social%20media%20platform%20X%2C%20formerly%20Twitter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20an%20incredible%20privilege%20to%20follow%20in%20the%20footsteps%20of%20legends%20like%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FTrevornoah%5C%22%3E%20%40Trevornoah%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20A.S.%20Byatt%20and%20Barbara%20Ehrenreich%2C%E2%80%9D%20