scussions%2C%20it%20was%20resolved%20that%20since%20by%202036%2C%20Odisha%20will%20complete%20100%20years%20of%20its%20statehood%26quot%3B%2C%20the%20BJD%20would%20do%20everything%20towards%20this%20in%20the%20greater%20interest%20of%20the%20people%20of%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20split%2C%20the%20BJD%20has%20consolidated%20its%20position%20in%20the%20state%2C%20making%20gains%20in%20both%20the%20Vidhan%20Sabha%20and%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%2C%20albeit%20ceding%20some%20ground%20to%20the%20BJP%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBJP%20Stands%20To%20Gain%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20it's%20evident%20why%20the%20BJP%20would%20seek%20the%20support%20of%20the%20BJD%20to%20realise%20its%20'Mission%20400'%20for%20the%20NDA%2C%20it%20remains%20unclear%20why%20the%20latter%20would%20seek%20a%20tie-up%20with%20the%20BJP%20at%20this%20juncture.%20Surveys%20indicate%20a%20close%20contest%20in%20Odisha%2C%20with%20the%20BJD%20projected%20to%20win%2011%20seats%20and%20the%20BJP%2010%20(CNX).%20Additionally%2C%20the%20BJD%20faces%20no%20significant%20anti-incumbency%20sentiment%20in%20the%20state%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fups-yogi-adityanath-second-most-popular-chief-minister-first-is-naveen-patnaik-odisha-5078371%5C%22%3ENaveen%20Patnaik%3C%2Fa%3E%20remains%20the%20most%20popular%20chief%20minister%20within%20the%20state%2C%20as%20per%20C-Voter's%20Mood%20of%20the%20Nation%20Survey%20in%20January%202024%2C%20and%20ranks%20fifth%20across%20India.%20His%20non-aligned%20approach%20has%20been%20successful%20thus%20far.%20Despite%20being%20out%20of%20the%20NDA%2C%20the%20BJD%20has%20supported%20the%20BJP%20in%20passing%20important%20bills%20in%20both%20houses%20of%20Parliament%2C%20with%20its%20backing%20being%20crucial%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESimultaneous%20Polls%20%26amp%3B%20Split%20Voting%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20has%20conducted%20simultaneous%20polls%20since%202004.%20Until%202014%2C%20it%20witnessed%20a%20consistent%20voting%20pattern%2C%20with%20voters%20typically%20voting%20for%20the%20same%20party%2C%20the%20BJD%2C%20in%20both%20assembly%20and%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections.%20The%20vote%20share%20of%20the%20BJD%20in%20both%20assembly%20and%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%20from%202004%20to%202019%20indicates%20that%20the%20party%20garners%20a%20nearly%20identical%20vote%20share%20in%20both%20elections%2C%20with%20deviations%20within%20the%20range%20of%20%2B%2F-%202.5%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202014%2C%20the%20BJD%20secured%20117%20of%20the%20total%20147%20seats%2C%20the%20BJP%2010%2C%20and%20the%20Congress%2016%20in%20the%20assembly%20elections.%20When%20translated%20to%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%2C%20the%20projection%20should%20have%20been%2018%20for%20the%20BJD%2C%20one%20for%20the%20BJP%2C%20and%20two%20for%20the%20Congress.%20Remarkably%2C%20the%20actual%20outcome%20closely%20mirrored%20this%20projection%2C%20with%20the%20BJD%20securing%2020%20seats%20and%20the%20BJP%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20some%20degree%20of%20split%20voting%20was%20observed.%20The%20BJD%20won%20112%20seats%2C%20the%20BJP%2023%2C%20and%20Congress%20nine%20in%20the%20assembly%20polls.%20When%20translated%20to%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%2C%20the%20projection%20should%20have%20been%20BJD%2017%2C%20BJP%20three%2C%20and%20Congress%20one.%20However%2C%20the%20actual%20result%20was%2012-8-1%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Couple%20Of%20Reasons%20The%20BJD%20May%20Consider%20Joining%20The%20NDA%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ENaveen%20Patnaik%2C%20at%2077%2C%20seems%20to%20lack%20confidence%20while%20facing%20a%20resurgent%20BJP%20under%20Narendra%20Modi%20after%20the%202024%20polls%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFailure%20to%20join%20the%20alliance%20before%20the%20polls%20could%20diminish%20Patnaik's%20bargaining%20power%20post-elections%2C%20particularly%20if%20the%20BJP%20does%20well%20on%20its%20own.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20BJP's%20reduced%20dependence%20on%20the%20BJD%20may%20occur%20as%20the%20BJP%20and%20allies%20increase%20their%20numbers%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20likely%20achieving%20a%20majority%20independently%20in%20mid-April%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EA%20leadership%20vacuum%20exists%20in%20the%20BJD%20post-Naveen%20era%2C%20with%20a%20potential%20successor%20in%20ex-bureaucrat%20V.K.%20Pandian.%20Naveen%20requires%20the%20BJP's%20support%20for%20a%20smooth%20transition%20of%20power%20upon%20his%20retirement%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ERegional%20parties%20like%20the%20BJD%20and%20the%20Janata%20Dal%20(United)%20(JD-U)%2C%20lacking%20familial%20successors%2C%20are%20cautious%20of%20scenarios%20akin%20to%20the%20Shiv%20Sena%20or%20the%20Nationalist%20Congress%20Party%20(NCP).%20Naveen%20may%20align%20with%20the%20BJP%20to%20safeguard%20his%20party's%20legacy%20and%20strength%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EConcerns%20arise%20over%20a%20potential%20exodus%20of%20dissatisfied%20leaders%20due%20to%20Pandian's%20outsider%20status.%20Fear%20persists%20that%20the%20BJP%20could%20exploit%20Odia%20sub-nationalism%2C%20eroding%20the%20BJD's%20support%20base%20and%20electoral%20prospects%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20BJP's%20aggressive%20expansion%20in%20eastern%20and%20southern%20states%2C%20leveraging%20the%20PM's%20popularity%20and%20development%20initiatives%2C%20may%20pose%20a%20threat%20to%20the%20BJD's%20Lok%20Sabha%20poll%20performance%2C%20potentially%20diminishing%20Naveen's%20national%20influence%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAligning%20with%20the%20BJP%20could%20enable%20Naveen%20to%20become%20the%20longest-serving%20chief%20minister%2C%20securing%20his%20place%20in%20history%20books%2C%20trailing%20behind%20Pawan%20Kumar%20Chamling%20by%20a%20mere%20164%20days%20as%20of%20March%207%2C%202024%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20BJD%20fears%20potential%20losses%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20if%20the%20split%20voting%20pattern%20expands%20across%20more%20constituencies%2C%20as%20discussed%20above%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWith%20Odisha%20approaching%20its%20centenary%20in%202036%2C%20resources%20are%20needed%20to%20make%20the%20occasion%20big.%20Aligning%20with%20the%20BJP%20could%20facilitate%20access%20to%20funds%20for%20Naveen's%20development%20plans%20for%20a%20%26quot%3BNaya%20Odisha%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20proposed%20alliance%20with%20the%20BJP%20may%20offer%20an%20opportunity%20for%20the%20Congress%20in%20the%20state%20to%20consolidate%20the%20opposition%20vote.%20Whether%20it%20can%20capitalise%20on%20this%20remains%20uncertain.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Amitabh%20Tiwari%20is%20a%20political%20strategist%20and%20commentator.%20In%20his%20earlier%20avatar%2C%20he%20was%20a%20corporate%20and%20investment%20banker.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709892840000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-05%2F6e9k6vk_naveen-patnaik-modi_625x300_11_May_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fwhy-is-naveen-patnaiks-bjd-keen-to-rejoin-bjp-led-nda-5199843%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Surveys%20indicate%20a%20close%20contest%20in%20Odisha%2C%20with%20the%20BJD%20projected%20to%20win%2011%20seats%20and%20the%20BJP%20ten.%20Also%2C%20the%20BJD%20faces%20no%20significant%20anti-incumbency%20in%20the%20state%20elections.%20But%20there%20are%20other%20reasons%20why%20it%20may%20consider%20joining%20the%20NDA...%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fwhy-is-naveen-patnaiks-bjd-keen-to-rejoin-bjp-led-nda-5199843%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fwhy-is-naveen-patnaiks-bjd-keen-to-rejoin-bjp-led-nda-5199843%2Famp%2F1%2