3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20jazz%2C%20the%20fewer%20the%20number%20of%20players%20the%20more%20difficult%20it%20gets.%20So%20the%20trio%20is%20a%20more%20difficult%20format%20than%20the%20quartet%20or%20the%20quintet%20for%20example.%20Of%20course%20the%20duet%20then%2C%20logically%2C%20is%20more%20difficult%20than%20a%20trio.%20In%20jazz%20literature%2C%20the%20voice%20and%20guitar%20combo%20is%20not%20too%20common.%20To%20that%20extent%2C%20Radha%2C%20who%20normally%20prefers%20to%20play%20with%20keyboard%20players%2C%20has%20changed%20gears%20with%20this%20album.%C2%A0%20For%20a%20singer%20with%20roots%20in%20rock%2C%20she%20does%20an%20excellent%20job%20with%20jazz%20which%20I%20am%20sure%20is%20now%20her%20first%20love.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBesides%20the%20proficiency%20of%20the%20vocalist%2C%20there%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20pressure%20on%20the%20instrumentalist%2C%20the%20guitarist%20in%20this%20case%20who%20has%20to%20weave%20in%20a%20few%20solo%20melodic%20lines%20along%20with%20the%20simultaneous%20bass%20lines%20to%20make%20the%20accompaniment%20sound%20full%20so%20that%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20miss%20the%20other%20instruments.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F08143013%2Funnamed.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F08143013%2Funnamed.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F08143013%2Funnamed-300x300.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F08143013%2Funnamed-1024x1024.png%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F08143013%2Funnamed-150x150.png%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-700768%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPhoto%3A%20By%20arrangement%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERadha%20Thomas%20has%20found%203%20very%20proficient%20guitarists%20who%20did%20a%20great%20job%20of%20soloing%20in%20between%20verses.%20The%20album%20also%20has%20some%20of%20my%20favourite%20standards.%20Here%20are%20a%20few%20of%20my%20favourite%20tracks.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20album%20starts%20with%20that%20old%20George%20Gershwin%20favourite%20from%20Porgy%20and%20Bess%2C%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrive.google.com%2Ffile%2Fd%2F1J42OdM_bE47O8H7PAJGT1c8Jlfa_8bBy%2Fview%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESummertime%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cspan%3Ewhich%20is%20always%20a%20challenge%20because%20it%20is%20the%20most%20overdone%20song%20in%20jazz%20and%20every%20dilettante%E2%80%99s%20favourite.%20Radha%20plays%20with%20the%20words%20to%20scat%20and%20refresh%20this%20old%20favourite.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20sings%20another%20one%20of%20my%20favourites%2C%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20could%20be%20happen%20to%20you%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ewhich%C2%A0%20was%20composed%20by%20Jimmy%20Van%20Heusen%20with%20lyrics%20by%20Johnny%20Burke.%20It%20first%20appeared%20in%20the%20Paramount%20musical%20comedy%20%3Cem%3EAnd%20the%20Angels%20Sing%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%201943.%20Chet%20Baker%20fans%20will%20remember%20that%20this%20was%20one%20of%20his%20favourites%20which%20he%20injected%20with%20an%20overdose%20of%20melancholy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98I%20fall%20in%20love%20too%20easily%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0was%20introduced%20by%20Frank%20Sinatra%20in%201945%20in%20the%20film%20%3Cem%3EAnchors%20Aweigh%3C%2Fem%3E.%20I%20am%20sorry%20to%20repeat%20myself%2C%20but%20I%20can%E2%80%99t%20help%20thinking%20of%20Baker%20once%20again.%20The%20lyrics%20in%20those%20days%20were%20so%20universal%20that%20they%20could%20apply%20to%20many%20of%20us.%C2%A0%20They%20also%20propounded%20a%20general%20philosophy%20on%20love%20and%20life.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20fall%20in%20love%20too%20easily%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20fall%20in%20love%20too%20fast%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20fall%20in%20love%20too%20terribly%20hard%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20love%20to%20ever%20last%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EDaahoud%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ewas%20an%20album%20by%20Max%20Roach%20and%20Clifford%20Brown%2C%20who%20later%20died%20in%20a%20car%20crash.%20Daahoud%20is%20the%20Arabic%20equivalent%20of%20David%20or%20my%20beloved.%20Brown%20named%20the%20song%20after%20a%20friend%20of%20his%20called%20Talib%20Dawud.%20Jazz%20folklore%20has%20it%20that%20he%20was%20also%20his%20drug%20dealer.%20This%20is%20actually%20a%20consummate%20instrumental%20track%20for%20horns%20but%20Radha%20weaves%20through%20the%20melody%20with%20ease.%20Her%20choice%20of%20the%20guitarists%20for%20this%20album%20is%20commendable.%20The%203%20guitarists%20%E2%80%93%20Reg%20Shwager%2C%20Pete%20McCann%20and%20Paul%20Meyers%20%E2%80%93%20have%20compatible%20styles%20of%20playing%20the%20jazz%20guitar%20so%20the%20tracks%20move%20seamlessly%20from%20one%20to%20the%20other%20with%20no%20stylistic%20change.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERadha%20wet%20her%20feet%20as%20a%20singer%20by%20singing%20with%20the%20Human%20Bondage%2C%20a%20premier%20rock%20band%20in%20India%20in%20the%2070s.%C2%A0%20She%20then%20developed%20a%20strong%20liking%20to%20jazz%20and%20later%20left%20for%20New%20York%20to%20pursue%20her%20ambition%20of%20being%20a%20jazz%20singer.%20With%20day%20jobs%20in%20travel%20and%20publishing%2C%20she%20sang%20in%