much%20so%20that%20some%20Meta%20employees%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftemu-millions-on-meta-ads-staff-joked-gift-card-rewards-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejoked%20they%20should%20thank%20Temu%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20giving%20it%20a%20gift%20card.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20Big%20Tech%20companies%20have%20also%20enjoyed%20the%20benefits%20of%20Temu's%20swollen%20ad%20budget.%20The%20company%20made%20its%20way%20into%20Google's%20Top%205%20advertisers%2C%20too%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Journal's%20report.%20And%20Pinterest's%20CEO%20pointed%20out%20the%20Temu%20effect%20during%20a%20recent%20earnings%20call%2C%20calling%20it%20%26quot%3Ba%20nice%20%E2%80%A6%20contributor.%26quot%3B%20(It%20also%20spent%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20on%20three%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftemu-spends-millions-super-bowl-ads-effort-win-us-users-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESuper%20Bowl%20ads%3C%2Fa%3E.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-temu-chinese-app-amazon-safe-legit-pinduoduo-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETemu%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20division%20of%20China-based%20PDD%20Holdings%2C%20which%20also%20operates%20Pinduoduo%20in%20that%20country.%20It's%20deployed%20a%20well-known%20playbook%20of%20doing%20a%20massive%20ad%20spend%20on%20social%20to%20acquire%20customers%20and%20get%20app%20downloads.%20This%20is%20all%20apparently%20in%20hopes%20that%20such%20a%20big%20ad%20spend%20will%20pay%20off%20later.%20Sometimes%2C%20this%20works%3B%20sometimes%2C%20it%20doesn't.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fwhat-is-wish-app%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWish%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20Chinese%20e-commerce%20app%2C%20made%20this%20same%20move%20in%20the%20late%202010s%2C%20but%20it%20fizzled%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20seems%20to%20be%20working%20now%3A%20Temu%20was%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftemu-us-e-commerce-700-percent-growth-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esecond%20fastest-growing%20website%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%202023%2C%20only%20second%20to%20OpenAI.%20One%20report%20found%20that%20nearly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftemu-is-on-a-quest-to-take-over-america-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1%20out%20of%203%20shoppers%20in%20the%20US%20had%20used%20Temu.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ETemu's%20ad%20spending%20is%20lining%20Meta's%20and%20Google's%20pockets%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20and%20Google%20are%20probably%20pleased%20with%20the%20ad%20revenue%20for%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmetas-profits-first-ever-dividend-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeta%20just%20posted%20record%20profits%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20last%20quarter%20and%20has%20a%20soaring%20stock%20price%2C%20with%20a%20brief%20mention%20in%20its%20earnings%20report%20that%2010%25%20of%20its%20global%20ad%20revenue%20came%20from%20Chinese%20e-commerce%20and%20gaming%20ads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there's%20something%20strange%20there.%20John%20Herrman%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnymag.com%2Fintelligencer%2Farticle%2Fbig-tech-still-has-a-big-addiction-to-china.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20Magazine%3C%2Fa%3E%20noticed%20a%20paradox%20in%20how%20Big%20Tech%20is%20very%20happy%20to%20publicly%20distance%20itself%20from%20connection%20to%20China.%20(Meta%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Ftechnology%2F2022%2F03%2F30%2Ffacebook-tiktok-targeted-victory%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehappy%20to%20throw%20Tiktok%20under%20the%20bus%3C%2Fa%3E.)%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20Herrman%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Chinese-American%20tech%20interdependence%20has%20by%20many%20measures%20%3Cem%3Eincreased%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Ad-supported%20firms%20like%20Meta%20and%20Google%20have%20benefited%20from%20massive%20spending%20from%20firms%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-shein-billion-dollar-fast-fashion-company-explained-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EShein%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Temu%3B%20online%20retailers%20including%20but%20not%20limited%20to%20Amazon%20have%20become%2C%20effectively%2C%20conduits%20for%20a%20new%20form%20of%20direct%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fbusiness%2Fu-s-trade-loophole-fuels-rise-of-chinas-new-e-commerce-firms-05cf2e05%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eloophole-enabled%3C%2Fa%3E%20cross-border%20commerce.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20shopped%20at%20Temu%2C%20and%20as%20someone%20who%20loves%20cheap%20junk%2C%20I%20see%20the%20appeal.%20But%20there%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftemu-blamed-shoppers-for-buying-forced-labor-lawmakers-say-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eserious%20concerns%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20potential%20forced%20labor%20practices%20at%20its%20suppliers%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20also%20how%20the%20addictive%20nature%20of%20cheap%2C%20gamified%20shopping%20can%20lead%20to%20our%20junk%20pile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222860%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22screenshot%20of%20Temu's%20website%20shows%20flash%20deals%20across%20the%20screen%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ad7a1b8ed31300199e71ca%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETemu%20is%20an%20online%20marketplace%20and%20mobile%20shopping%20app%20that%20offers%20daily%20flash%20deals.%3Cp%3EScreenshot%2FTemu%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there's%20something%20else%20going%20on%20that%20might%20worry%20companies%20like%20Google%20and%20Meta%20that%20are%20enjoying%20the%20Temu%20ad%20bonanza.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F7062735d-43c5-4570-ac11-bc929ea0f297%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Financial%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20a%20big%20investigation%20into%20Temu's%20parent%20company%20PDD%20and%20concluded%20that%20it's%20mysterious%20in%20ways%20that%20publicly%20traded%20companies%20normally%20aren't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMystery%20surrounds%20basics%20like%20who%20owns%20the%20company%2C%20where%20its%20offices%20are%20located%2C%20and%20straightforward%20aspects%20of%20its%20business%20model%20and%20financials%2C%20like%20what%20the%20gross%20value%20of%20its%20merchandise%20is%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3EWhy%20does%20PDD%20look%20like%20much%20smaller%20peers%20when%20staff%20levels%20and%20research%20spending%20are%20compared%3F%20Why%20haven't%20competitors%20described%20the%20impact%20of%20PDD's%20rise%3F%20Why%20do%20balance%20sheet%20metrics%20move%20at%20a%20different%20pace%20to%20revenues%3F%20How%20does%20a%20%24200bn%20company%20own%20less%20than%20%24150mn%20worth%20of%20hard%20assets%3F%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Financial%20Times%20investigation%20makes%20a%20strong%20case%20that%20Temu's%20parent%20company%20is%20indeed%20mysterious%20and%20very%20unlike%20other%20Chinese%20e-commerce%20competitors%20like%20Alibaba.%20But%20it's%20not%20clear%20what%20conclusion%20we%20should%20draw.%20(A%20PDD%20spokesperson%20told%20the%20FT%20that%20it%20%26quot%3Bdisagreed%26quot%3B%20with%20the%20characterization%20of%20its%20company%20as%20opaque.)%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMysterious%20advertisers%20might%20raise%20red%20flags%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20for%20Meta%20and%20Google%2C%20I%20would%20humbly%20suggest%20that%20it%20may%20not%20be%20a%20great%20thing%20if%20one%20of%20your%20top%20advertisers%20has%20an%20opaque%20and%20mysterious%20business%20model%20that%20is%20the%20subject%20of%20a%20splashy%20media%20investigation%20into%20how%20no%20one%20seems%20to%20know%20how%20it%20makes%20money.%20(Temu%20didn't%20immediately%20respond%20to%