ent%20protests%20by%20Southern%20state%20governments%2C%20notably%20Kerala%20and%20Karnataka%2C%20supported%20by%20other%20non-Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party-ruled%20states%2C%20have%20highlighted%20concerns%20regarding%20fiscal%20federalism%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ffiscal-federalism-finance-commission-states-taxes%5C%22%3EFiscal%20federalism%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20concerned%20with%20understanding%20which%20functions%20and%20instruments%20are%20best%20centralised%20and%20which%20are%20best%20placed%20in%20the%20sphere%20of%20decentralised%20levels%20of%20government.%20It%20involves%20vertical%20and%20horizontal%20dimensions.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithin%20the%20domain%20of%20vertical%20devolution%2C%20which%20includes%20sharing%20of%20resources%20between%20the%20Union%20and%20states%2C%20there%20are%20two%20disturbing%20trends%20that%20need%20urgent%20redressal%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fnramind%2Fstatus%2F1763118170003718309%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Eargued%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20professor%20R.%20Ramakumar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EDon%E2%80%99t%20miss%20this%20data-backed%2C%20lucid%2C%20and%20important%20analysis%20in%20The%20Hindu%20by%20Professor%20R.%20Ramakumar%20of%20how%20States%20are%20done%20out%20of%20their%20rightful%20share%20of%20the%20net%20divisible%20pool%20of%20revenues%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20and%20how%20the%20practice%20of%20fiscal%20federalism%20in%20India%20is%20deeply%20flawed.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FlBTuPNR7Fw%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FlBTuPNR7Fw%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20N.%20Ram%20(%40nramind)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fnramind%2Fstatus%2F1763118170003718309%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EFebruary%2029%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERamakumar%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fnramind%2Fstatus%2F1763118170003718309%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Eargues%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20is%20keeping%20more%20of%20its%20earnings%20out%20of%20the%20divisible%20pool%20to%20avoid%20sharing%20with%20states.%20It%E2%80%99s%20also%20not%20devolving%20the%20share%20of%20net%20proceeds%20to%20the%20states%2C%20as%20mandated%20by%20successive%20Finance%20Commissions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECentral%20taxes%20that%20are%20shared%20with%20states%20go%20into%20a%20divisible%20pool%2C%20while%20cesses%20and%20surcharges%20are%20excluded.%20The%20share%20of%20the%20latter%20has%20increased%20from%20around%2010%25%20in%202011-12%20to%20as%20much%20as%2025%25%20in%202021-22.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20increase%20in%20the%20size%20of%20the%20tax%20kitty%20owing%20to%20cesses%20and%20surcharges%20is%20being%20appropriated%20by%20the%20Centre%20via%20subterfuge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20the%20increasing%20constraints%20on%20political%20freedom%20are%20evidence%20of%20how%20the%20constitutionally%20safeguarded%20practice%20of%20fiscal%20federalism%20is%20being%20affected.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20has%20weaponised%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthe-convenient-doublespeak-of-modi-over-centres-fiscal-injustice-towards-states%5C%22%3E%20fiscal%20devolution%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20meeting%20political%20ends%2C%20especially%20in%20its%20conflict%20with%20the%20non-BJP%20state%20governments%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fbranding-over-welfare-union-withholds-funds-from-bengal-for-not-displaying-pm-photo-at-ration-shops%5C%22%3EWest%20Bengal%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fkerala-union-government-supreme-court-borrowing-capacity%5C%22%3EKerala%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ffiscal-injustice-powers-a-new-axis-of-protest-against-modi-govt%5C%22%3EKarnataka%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Ffederalism-vs-14th-finance-commission%5C%22%3ETamil%20Nadu%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20to%20name%20a%20few.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%E2%80%99s%20another%20concern%3A%20the%20issue%20of%20goods%20and%20services%20tax%2C%20or%20GST.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20terms%20of%20magnitude%20of%20GST%20revenues%2C%20states%20have%20done%20well%20since%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Csingle%20unified%20market%E2%80%9D%20via%20the%20introduction%20of%20the%20GST%20came%20about%20in%202017.%20However%2C%20this%20increased%20volume%20of%20revenue%2C%20anchored%20by%20temporal%20reasons%20of%20increased%20revenue-share%2C%20came%20at%20a%20huge%20price%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20true%20spirit%20of%20democratic%20federalism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20any%20voting%20exercise%20within%20the%20GST%20Council%2C%20the%20Centre%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-voting-at-the-gst-council-6206947%2F%5C%22%3Ecarries%20a%20weight%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20one-third%20(33.33%25)%2C%20with%20the%20balance%20two-thirds%20(66.67%25)%20shared%20by%20the%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20for%20a%20proposal%20to%20be%20approved%2C%20it%20needs%20the%20support%20of%2075%25%20of%20the%20total%20voting%20weight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%20is%20now%20in%20power%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Felections%2Fstory%2Fbjp-political-map-landscape-after-latest-win-assembly-elections-congress-india-electoral-map-and-road-to-2024-lok-sabha-elections-2471578-2023-12-04%5C%22%3E12%20of%20the%2028%20states%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20India%20and%20is%20in%20the%20ruling%20coalition%20in%20four%20others.%20And%20in%20December%202019%2C%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Fend-of-consensus-as-gst-council-takes-voting-route%2Fstory-NFhpsIUG2aO1yysQA1JkfJ.html%5C%22%3Ehad%20shifted%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20voting%20from%20its%20tradition%20of%20taking%20consensus-based%20decisions%20to%20settle%20all%20matters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20governments%20have%20also%20lost%20their%20ability%20to%20independently%20collect%20revenue%20from%20the%20sales%20tax.%20Additionally%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20trend%20towards%20centralisation%20of%20power%20in%20politics%2C%20which%20could%20reduce%20states%E2%80%99%20ability%20to%20find%20new%20revenue%20sources%20or%20borrow%20money%20for%20their%20expenses%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEach%20of%20these%20issues%20merit%20wider%20attention%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20upcoming%20general%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20aggrieved%20states%E2%80%99%20perspective%2C%20there%20are%20three%20key%20principles%20that%20can%20ensure%20a%20better%20partnership%20based%20on%20trust%20and%20a%20more%20robust%20federal-finance%20relationship%20between%20the%20Centre%20and%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Famid-indias-silent-fiscal-crisis-and-fragile-federalism-16th-finance-commission-has-an-uphill-task%5C%22%3EAmid%20India%E2%80%99s%20Silent%20Fiscal%20Crisis%20and%20Fragile%20Federalism%2C%2016th%20Finance%20Commission%20Has%20an%20Uphill%20Task%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVertical%20equity%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20principle%20of%20vertical%20equity%20in%20public%20finance%20entrusts%20a%20government%20to%20ask%20those%20who%20earn%20more%20or%20have%20a%20higher%20wealth%20to%20pay%20more%20in%20their%20share%20of%20contributed%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20a%20complex%20system%20of%20intergovernmental%20fiscal%20relations.%20This%20complexity%20has%20its%20roots%20in%20a%20number%20of%20factors%2C%20including%20ethnic%2C%20social%2C%20and%20economic%20disparities%20among%20states%2Fregions%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20long-standing%20vertical-imbalance%20between%20the%20expenditure%20and%20revenue%20raising%20responsibilities%20of%20the%20state%20governments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20imbalance%20in%20the%20past%20was%20covered%20by%20revenue-sharing%20arrangements%2C%20in%20which%20states%2C%20particularly%20developing%20states%2C%20received%20a%20variety%20of%20grants%20from%20the%20Centre.%20Even%20if%20grants%20are%20not%20allocated%2C%20the%20Centre%20can%20do%20more%20in%20reducing%20the%20cesses%2Fsurcharge%20composition%20in%20the%20macro-tax%20weightage%2C%20while%20imposing%20a%20larger%20share%20of%20direct%20tax%20burden%20on%20the%20top%2010%25%20of%20the%20wealth-asset%20endowed%20class%2C%20safeguarding%20a%20larger%20devolved%20proportion%20of%20that%20%E2%80%98tax%E2%80%99%20revenue%20for%20states%2C%20that%20need%20additional%20resources.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20author%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fconsumption-based-tax-system-reform-india%5C%22%3Ehad%20earlier%20discussed%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20proposal%20to%20levy%20a%20%E2%80%98consumption%20tax%E2%80%99%20on%20the%20richer%20(top%2010%25)%20asset%20class%2C%20consuming%20a%20larger%20proportion%20of%20luxury%20goods%2C%20that%20can%20help%20them%20pay%20more%20as%20compared%20to%20other%20classes%20who%20pay%20a%20similar%20amount%20of%20tax%20(in%20case%20of%20GST%20or%20other%20indirectly%20imposed%20tax)%20irrespective%20of%20the%20income%20they%20earn%20or%20the%20wealth%20they%20endow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EProportionality%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProportionality%2C%20in%20a%20jurisprudence%20sense%20of%20public%20law%20and%20political%20theory%2C%20appeals%20to%20%E2%80%98reason%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98reasonable%E2%80%99%20conduct%20for%20the%20way%20a%20court%20sentences%20a%20convict%2C%20or%20how%20a%20parliamentary%20body%20or%20executive%20may%20choose%20to%20function.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20cannot%20(or%20shouldn%E2%80%99t)%20use%20a%20cannon%20to%20fire%20a%20sparrow.%20Balancing%20means%20with%20ends%20matters.%20The%20Finance%20Commission%20has%20a%20mandate%20in%20recommending%20ways%20for%20the%20central%20government%20to%20be%20more%20reasonable%20and%20proportionate%20in%20the%20way%20they%20organise%20their%20devolution%20framework%20with%20the%20states%20in%20a%20time-sensitive%20and%20needs-based%20manner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20time%20when%20the%20federal%20faith%20and%20mutual%20trust%20in%20the%20Centre-state%20relations%20have%20taken%20a%20more%20%E2%80%98uncooperative%E2%80%99%20turn%2C%20largely%20due%20to%20political%20factors%2C%20it%20would%20be%20interesting%20to%20see%20how%20the%20new%2016th%20Finance%20Commission%20handles%20this%20growing%20friction%20back%20to%20its%20original%20charter%3A%20of%20ensuring%20%E2%80%98pooled%20sovereignty%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20truest%20sense.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJuridical%20precedence%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20of%20pooled%20sovereignty%2C%20seen%20as%20foundational%20to%20the%20functioning%20of%20the%20GST%2C%20has%20come%20under%20threat%20due%20to%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2020%2F23083%2F23083_2020_4_1501_35969_Judgement_19-May-2022.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EUnion%20of%20India%20vs.%20Mohit%20Minerals%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20which%20a%20three-judge%20bench%2C%20presided%20by%20now%20Chief%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%2C%20explained%20by%20Gautam%20Bhatia%20recently%2C%20held%20that%20the%20GST%20Council%E2%80%99s%20decisions%20are%20not%20binding%20on%20legislative%20bodies%20and%20that%20both%20Parliament%20and%20state%20legislatures%20possess%20plenary%20powers%20to%20make%20laws%20as%20they%20deem%20fit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20examining%20the%20case%20that%20came%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20the%20bench%20considered%20the%20purport%20of%20Article%20279A%20and%20made%20a%20series%20of%20findings%2C%20explained%20by%20Bhatia%2C%20which%20could%20%E2%80%9Cpotentially%20dismantle%20the%20idea%20of%20GST%20as%20understood%20through%20the%20101st%20amendment%E2%80%9D%20(via%20which%20the%20legal%20way%20for%20creating%20a%20GST%20was%20made%20possible).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20recognised%20that%20the%20GST%20Council%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Crecommendations%E2%80%9D%20cannot%20be%20observed%20as%20binding%20(on%20states)%20since%20it%20would%20violate%20the%20supremacy%20of%20Parliament%20and%20the%20state-legislatures%20since%20both%20have%20been%20afforded%20%E2%80%9Csimultaneous%E2%80%9D%20legislative%20power%20on%20GST.%20Secondly%2C%20the%20virtual%20veto%20given%20to%20the%20Union%20in%20the%20GST%20Council%20would%20lead%20to%20a%20violation%20of%20fiscal%20federalism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20the%20two%20federal%20principles%20discussed%2C%20the%20court%20in%20this%20case%20has%20provided%20a%20strong%20juridical%20precedence%20for%20states%20to%20exercise%20their%20parliamentary%20power%20and%20not%20see%20the%20GST%20Council%E2%80%99s%20recommendations%20as%20binding%2C%20when%20the%20Centre%20refuses%20to%20act%20in%20a%20%E2%80%98reasonable%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98proportionate%E2%80%99%20manner%2C%20in%20its%20own%20devolution%20practice%20for%20either%20political%20or%20any%20other%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2016th%20Finance%20Commission%20must%20address%20and%20resolve%20critical%20issues%20such%20as%20the%20sharing%20of%20resources%20from%20the%20divisible%20pool%20and%20the%20extent%20of%20cesses%20and%20surcharges.%20There%20are%20historical%20wrongs%20in%20vertical%20devolution%20that%20merit%20greater%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20political%20will%20to%20engage%20with%20principles%2C%20due%20process%2C%20and%20constitutional%20morals%2C%20as%20evident%20in%20the%20fiscal%20conduct%20of%20the%20Centre%20%E2%80%93%20which%20has%20put%20political%20means%20over%20anything%20else%20in%20its%20relationship%20with%20states%20and%20other%20institutions%20%E2%80%93%20how%20and%20to%20what%20extent%20the%20Finance%20Commission%20addresses%20these%20issues%20with%20an%20%E2%80%98independent%2C%20non-partisan%20mandate%E2%80%99%20will%20remain%20a%20question%20to%20be%20answered%20on%20its%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDeepanshu%20Mohan%20is%20Professor%20of%20Economics%2C%20Dean%2C%20the%20Office%20of%20Interdisciplinarity%20and%20Director%2C%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%20(CNES)%20at%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University.%20He%20is%20a%20Visiting%20Professor%20at%20the%20London%20School%20of%20Economics%20and%20Political%20Science%20and%20has%20Visiting%20positions%20at%20University%20of%20London%2C%20University%20of%20Ottawa%2C%20Stellenbosch%20University%20(to%20name%20a%20few).%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709888930000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F08142600%2Fimage-1921.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Fthe-16th-finance-commission-must-heed-3-principles-to-fix-resource-sharing-between-union-and-states%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Given%20the%20lack%20of%20political%20will%20to%20prioritise%20principles%2C%20due%20process%2C%20and%20constitutional%20integrity%2C%20how%20and%20to%20what%20extent%20the%20Commission%20addresses%20these%20issues%20with%20an%20'independent%2C%20non-partisan%20mandate'%20will%20remain%20a%20question%20requiring%20its%20own%20answer.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Fthe-16th-finance-commission-must-heed-3-principles-to-fix-resource-sharing-between-union-and-states%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20On%20Women's%20Day%2C%20A%20Question%20-%20When%20Will%20The%20Promised%20Best%20Arrive%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-03%2F1llu5qt_women-labour_625x300_08_March_19.jpg%3Fim%3DResize%3D(1230%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20began%20writing%20this%20essay%2C%20I%20had%20been%20reading%20Rona%20Jaffe's%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Best%20of%20Everything%3C%2Fem%3E.%C2%A0The%20date%20of%20its%20publication%2C%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fpm-modi-announces-rs-100-cut-in-cooking-gas-cylinder-prices-on-womens-day-5198224%5C%22%3EInternational%20Women's%20Day%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20was%20an%20added%20irony.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Jaffe's%20book%20came%20out%2066%20years%20ago%2C%20about%20a%20decade%20after%20Simone%20de%20Beauvoir's%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Second%20Sex%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20relationship%20between%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Finternational-womens-day-2024-un-lists-5-challenges-that-demand-our-attention-5198314%5C%22%3Ewomen%20and%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20rarely%20discussed%2C%20if%20at%20all.%20It%20mattered%20to%20either%20the%20intellectually%20curious%20few%20who%20engaged%20in%20philosophical%20inquiry%20on%20the%20subject%2C%20or%20the%20conscious%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Finternational-womens-day-president-droupadi-murmu-says-lets-remove-remaining-hurdles-from-path-of-young-women-5198299%5C%22%3Eworking%20woman%3C%2Fa%3E%20herself%20who%20was%20cognisant%20of%20her%20role%20in%20the%20second%20wave%20of%20feminism%20and%20what%20she%20aimed%20to%20achieve%20from%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20women%20in%20Jaffe's%20novels%20belonged%20to%20none%20of%20these%20categories.%20Like%20most%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fthe-key-to-fast-track-indias-progress-is-more-women-in-local-bodies-5198821%5C%22%3Eordinary%20women%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20saw%20work%2C%20at%20least%20initially%2C%20as%20a%20chapter%2C%20not%20a%20whole%20new%20world%20they%20were%20unknowingly%20participating%20in.%20For%20most%20of%20them%2C%20working%20life%20was%20either%20a%20financial%20necessity%20or%20just%20an%20interlude%20before%20the%20'more%20important'%20milestones%3A%20marriage%2C%20children%2C%20comfortable%20domesticity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20would%20think%20much%20would%20have%20changed%20in%20over%20half%20a%20century%20since%20then.%20That%20the%20idea%20of%20the%20working%20woman%20would've%20found%20its%20way%20out%20of%20mere%20academic%20musing%20to%20a%20more%20concrete%2C%20tangible%20framework%20that%20enabled%C2%A0that%20idea.%20To%20be%20fair%2C%20things%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ehave%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Echanged.%20But%20if%20the%20credit%20for%20that%20must%20go%20to%20anyone%2C%20it%20has%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fswachhindia.ndtv.com%2Finternational-womens-day-special-celebrating-the-work-of-women-in-india-who-are-helping-the-country-achieve-its-sustainable-development-goals-74439%2F%5C%22%3Ewomen%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20women%20alone.%20Their%20progress%20has%20largely%20-%20if%20not%20completely%20-%20been%20not%20because%20of%2C%20but%20%3Cem%3Edespite%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20world.%20A%20bunch%20of%20headlines%20from%20the%20month%20gone%20by%20prompt%20me%20to%20say%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Marriage%20No%20Ground%20For%20Sacking%20A%20Woman'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20what%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20to%20spell%20out%20last%20month%20as%20it%20heard%20a%20plea%20by%20the%20Centre%20challenging%20the%20decision%20of%20an%20Armed%20Forces%20Tribunal%20that%20ruled%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20reinstatement%20of%20a%20woman%20who%20was%20dismissed%20from%20her%20job.%20Selina%20John%2C%20a%20Lieutenant%20in%20the%20Military%20Nursing%20Service%20in%201988%2C%20had%20to%20leave%20because%20she%20got%20married.%20The%20rule%20that%20facilitated%20this%2C%20Army%20Instruction%20No.%2061%20of%201977%2C%20listed%20the%20grounds%20for%20the%20termination%20of%20an%20appointment%2C%20and%20in%20there%2C%20marriage%20was%20as%20much%20an%20infraction%20as%20breach%20of%20contract%20or%20misconduct.%20Though%20the%20rule%20was%20struck%20down%20in%201995%2C%20it%20took%20another%2030%20years%20for%20John%20to%20get%20a%20decision%20in%20her%20favour.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20unable%20to%20accept%20any%20submission%20that%20the%20respondent%20-%20Ex.%20Lt.%20Selina%20John%20-%20could%20have%20been%20released%2Fdischarged%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20she%20had%20got%20married.%20Such%20rule%20was%20ex-facie%20manifestly%20arbitrary%2C%20as%20terminating%20employment%20because%20the%20woman%20has%20got%20married%20is%20a%20coarse%20case%20of%20gender%20discrimination%20and%20inequality%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20observed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJohn's%20win%2C%20however%2C%20is%20not%20the%20norm%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20discrimination%20in%20the%20labour%20market.%20Crores%20of%20women%20in%20India%20are%20not%20even%20looking%20for%20work%2C%20for%20a%20variety%20of%20reasons%2C%20according%20to%20Oxfam's%202022%20%3Cem%3EIndia%20Discrimination%20Report%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20labour%20force%20participation%20rate%20(FLFPR)%20for%20women%20in%20India%20is%2037%25%2C%20which%20means%20just%20one%20in%20three%20women%20in%20India%20are%20either%20working%20or%20seeking%20work.%20For%20most%20women%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20unorganised%20sector%2C%20when%20they%20do%20get%20work%2C%20it's%20rarely%20long-term%20because%20demand%20remains%20erratic.%20Over%20half%20of%20the%20women%20who%20were%20in%20the%20labour%20force%20in%20at%20least%20a%20four-month%20period%20reported%20exiting%20or%20entering%20the%20workforce%20more%20than%20two%20times%2C%20according%20to%20a%20study%20published%20in%202021%20by%20the%20Institute%20of%20Labour%20Economics.%20Which%20means%20even%20if%20a%20woman%C2%A0is%C2%A0looking%20for%20work%2C%20stable%2C%20long-term%20employment%20is%20difficult%20to%20sustain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGender%20discrimination%20is%20almost%20%26quot%3Btotal%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20country%20-%20a%20100%25%20-%20the%20Oxfam%20report%20states.%20That%20is%2C%20all%20women%20are%20discriminated%20against%20in%20work%20regardless%20of%20their%20socioeconomic%20location.%20Gender-based%20discrimination%20is%20the%20reason%20for%2098%25%20of%20the%20employment%20gap%20between%20salaried%20males%20and%20females%20in%20urban%20areas%3B%20only%202%25%20can%20be%20attributed%20to%20endowments.%20In%20plainer%20words%2C%20it%20may%20not%20matter%20to%20an%20employer%20how%20qualified%20or%20educated%20a%20woman%20is%2C%20because%20she%20is%20a%20woman.%20That%20unjustness%20is%20more%20pronounced%20in%20rural%20areas%2C%20where%20women%20from%20families%20that%20have%20climbed%20up%20the%20economic%20ladder%20or%20gained%20some%20social%20capital%20tend%20to%20not%20even%20look%20for%20work%20due%20to%20sociocultural%20reasons.%20All%20this%20means%20that%20there%20are%20crores%20of%20well-qualified%2C%20educated%20women%20simply%20sitting%20outside%20of%20the%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Women%20Can't%20Be%20Denied%20Government%20Jobs%20Because%20Of%20Pregnancy'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Uttarakhand%20High%20Court%20observed%20last%20month%20as%20it%20struck%20down%20a%20rule%20that%20barred%20women%20who%20had%20been%20pregnant%20for%2012%20weeks%20or%20more%20from%20getting%20government%20jobs.%20The%20court%20was%20hearing%20a%20plea%20filed%20by%20a%20woman%20who%20was%20denied%20employment%20as%20a%20nursing%20officer%20at%20a%20government%20hospital%20after%20a%20fitness%20certificate%20declared%20her%20%26quot%3Btemporarily%20unfit%26quot%3B.%20%26quot%3BIf%20a%20situation%20is%20visualised%20that%20a%20woman%20who%20joins%20service%20on%20fresh%20appointment%20and%20becomes%20pregnant%20after%20joining%20would%20get%20maternity%20leave%2C%20then%20why%20can't%20a%20pregnant%20woman%20join%20her%20duties%20on%20fresh%20appointment%3F%20After%20joining%2C%20she%20would%20also%20be%20entitled%20to%20maternity%20leave%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20High%20Court%20observed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20court's%20intervention%20was%20necessary%2C%20the%20entitlement%20to%20maternity%20leave%20has%20become%20almost%20a%20Pyrrhic%20victory%20for%20women.%20Working%20mothers%20may%20have%20broken%20through%20the%20glass%20ceiling%2C%20it's%20the%20'maternal%20wall'%20that%20many%20struggle%20to%20scale.%20Denying%20women%20employment%20opportunities%20due%20to%20pregnancy%20is%20illegal%20under%20various%20laws%2C%20including%20the%20Code%20of%20Social%20Security%20and%20the%20Maternity%20Benefit%20Act.%20However%2C%20the%20maternal%20wall%20ensures%20that%20even%20if%20a%20woman%20employee%20is%20not%20terminated%2C%20her%20'performance'%20is%20often%20excessively%20scrutinised%20when%20she%20becomes%20a%20mother%2C%20applies%20for%20paid%20maternity%20leave%2C%20or%20requests%20flexible%20work%20schedules.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20when%20India%20extended%20maternity%20benefits%20from%2018%20to%2026%20weeks%2C%20experts%20highlighted%20that%20without%20adequate%20monitoring%20mechanisms%20and%20paternity%20leave%2C%20which%20would%20redistribute%20unpaid%20caregiving%20responsibilities%20between%20both%20parents%20and%20mitigate%20women%20from%20bearing%20the%20sole%20burden%20of%20career%20disruptions%20in%20the%20long%20term%2C%20employers%20would%20persist%20in%20disregarding%20the%20regulations.%20Consequently%2C%20maternity%20leave%20might%20even%20deter%20some%20employers%20from%20hiring%20women%20of%20childbearing%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20unorganised%20sector%2C%20women%20in%20infrastructure%20or%20construction%20jobs%20were%20declared%20eligible%20for%20maternity%20benefits%20only%20last%20month.%20While%20this%20is%20a%20welcome%20step%2C%20without%20additional%20safeguards%2C%20it%20may%20place%20the%20employability%20of%20women%20wage%20workers%20under%20a%20similar%20-%20in%20fact%2C%20a%20much%20heavier%20-%20strain%20than%20that%20faced%20by%20women%20in%20formal%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20this%20influences%20the%20pay%20disparity%20between%20men%20and%20women%2C%20with%20women%20often%20placed%20at%20a%20disadvantage%20as%20they%20balance%20work%20and%20personal%20responsibilities.%20Men%20capture%2082%25%20of%20the%20labour%20income%20in%20India.%20Women%2C%20only%2018%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20leads%20me%20to%20the%20next%20headline...%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Homemaker's%20Work%20No%20less%20Than%20Salary-Earning%20Spouse's'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20recent%20ruling%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20addressed%20a%20case%20involving%20the%20assessment%20of%20a%20housewife's%20notional%20income%2C%20which%20was%20deemed%20to%20be%20lower%20than%20that%20of%20a%20daily%20wage%20worker.%20The%20case%20arose%20from%20a%20motor%20accident%20that%20claimed%20a%20woman's%20life%2C%20prompting%20deliberation%20on%20the%20compensation%20owed%20to%20her%20family%20based%20on%20her%20life%20expectancy%20and%20hypothetical%20income.%20A%20tribunal%20determined%20her%20%26quot%3Bnotional%20income%26quot%3B%20to%20be%20less%20than%20that%20of%20a%20daily%20wage%20earner%2C%20a%20decision%20upheld%20by%20the%20High%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20role%20of%20a%20homemaker%20is%20as%20important%20as%20that%20of%20a%20family%20member%20whose%20income%20is%20tangible.%20If%20the%20activities%20performed%20by%20a%20homemaker%20are%20computed%20one%20by%20one%2C%20there%20cannot%20be%20any%20doubt%20that%20the%20contribution%20is%20of%20a%20high%20order%20and%20is%20invaluable.%20In%20fact%2C%20it%20is%20difficult%20to%20compute%20her%20contributions%20only%20in%20monetary%20terms%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20said%20as%20it%20differed%20with%20the%20High%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20sake%20of%20argument%20though%2C%20let's%20consider%20the%20monetary%20terms.%20All%20women%20work%2C%20very%20few%20are%20paid%20for%20it.%20Women's%20unpaid%20domestic%20work%20makes%20up%20as%20much%20as%207.5%25%20of%20India's%20Gross%20Domestic%20Product%2C%20or%20Rs%2022.7%20lakh%20crore%2C%20according%20to%20a%202023%20report%20by%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India.%20As%20many%20as%2092%25%20of%20women%20aged%2015-59%20years-%20irrespective%20of%20whether%20they're%20formally%20employed%20or%20not%20-%20are%20engaged%20in%20unpaid%20domestic%20work%2C%20compared%20to%20just%2021%25%20of%20men%2C%20India's%20First%20Time-Use%20Survey%20in%202019%20showed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWorking%20women%20bear%20a%20'double'%20burden.%20Despite%20their%20significant%20contribution%20to%20the%20economy%2C%20nearly%20no%20economic%20policy%20has%20effectively%20quantified%20women's%20unpaid%20work%2C%20which%20encompasses%20not%20only%20household%20chores%20but%20also%20agricultural%20labour%20on%20family%20farms%20or%20in%20animal%20husbandry%2C%20effectively%20subsidizing%20the%20costs%20of%20actual%20labour.%20Women%20are%20seldom%20acknowledged%20as%20'farmers'%20in%20India.%20Their%20labour%20remains%20invisible%20to%20policymakers%2C%20while%20the%20women%20themselves%20are%20often%20relegated%20to%20mere%20'dependents'%20of%20the%20predominantly%20male%20head%20of%20the%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Argument%20of%20Functional%20Difference%20Can't%20Work%20In%202024'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20again%20that%20last%20month%20took%20up%20the%20plea%20of%20a%20woman%20officer%20in%20the%20Indian%20Coast%20Guard%20who%20was%20seeking%20permanent%20commission.%20The%20Centre%20argued%20that%20the%20Coast%20Guard%20functions%20%26quot%3Ba%20little%20differently%26quot%3B%20from%20the%20Navy%20and%20the%20Army%2C%20where%20women%20are%20eligible%20for%20permanent%20commission.%20%26quot%3BAll%20this%20functionality%20etc.%20arguments%20do%20not%20hold%20water%20in%202024.%20Women%20cannot%20be%20left%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20shot%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat's%20glaringly%20evident%20in%20these%20headlines%20is%20the%20persistent%20and%20universal%20neglect%20towards%20developing%20a%20labour%20market%20that%20can%20accommodate%20a%20group%20constituting%20half%20of%20India's%20population.%20Jaffe's%20book%20begins%20with%20an%20advertisement%20from%20the%20New%20York%20Times%3A%20%26quot%3BYou%20deserve%20the%20best%20of%20everything%2C%20the%20best%20job%2C%20the%20best%20surroundings%2C%20the%20best%20pay%2C%20the%20best%20contacts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20will%20the%20promised%20best%20arrive%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPS%3A%20In%20other%20news%2C%20India's%20first%20human%20space%20flight%20programme%20will%20have%20no%20women%20as%20there%20were%20no%20female%20test%20pilots%20in%20the%20country%20at%20the%20time%20of%20selection.%20But%20the%20Indian%20Space%20Research%20Organisation%20(ISRO)%20is%20confident%20that%20it%20will%20be%20able%20to%20send%20women%20astronauts%20in%20space%20very%20soon.%20Till%20then%2C%20there%20is%20that%20female%20humanoid%20robot%2C%20'Vyommitra'%2C%20to%20make%20up%20for%20the%20cosmic%20absence.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(The%20author%20is%20Assistant%20Editor%2C%20Opinions%2C%20NDTV)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709888520000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-03%2F1llu5qt_women-labour_625x300_08