merely%20strike%20down%20the%20Colorado%20decision%2C%20it%20kicked%20the%20issue%20to%20the%20Congress%2C%20made%20it%20their%20job%20to%20decide%20the%20outcome%2C%20making%20it%20an%20overtly%20political%20decision%20they%20must%20know%20will%20never%20emerge%20from%20the%20current%20Congress%20of%20far%20right%20do%20nothings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20now%20has%20a%20free%20pass%2C%20a%20virtual%20%E2%80%98get%20out%20of%20jail%20free%E2%80%99%20card.%20The%20appetite%20for%20democracy%2C%20constitutional%20norms%2C%20and%20checks%20and%20balances%20among%20US%20elites%20is%20dying.%20It%20only%20just%20made%20it%20through%20on%20January%206%2C%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWill%20it%20scrape%20through%20in%20January%202025%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20majority%20corrupt%20right%20wing%20court%2C%20with%20liberal%20accomplices%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20that%20just%20ruled%20has%20three%20justices%20appointed%20by%20Trump%20(Barrett%2C%20Gorsuch%2C%20Kavanaugh)%2C%20two%20appointed%20by%20George%20W.%20Bush%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20contested%20election%20of%202000%20(Alito%2C%20Roberts)%2C%20and%20the%20controversial%20Clarence%20Thomas%20whose%20wife%20(Ginni%20Thomas)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbsnews.com%2Fsanfrancisco%2Fnews%2Fginni-thomas-tells-jan-6-committee-she-regrets-texting-with-meadows-about-2020-election%2F%5C%22%3Eplayed%20a%20key%20role%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20failed%20bid%20to%20overturn%20the%202020%20election.%20The%20standing%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20fallen%20through%20the%20floor%20due%20to%20well%20documented%20levels%20of%20corruption.%20Supreme%20Court%20justices%20are%20subject%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brennancenter.org%2Four-work%2Fanalysis-opinion%2Fnew-supreme-court-ethics-code-designed-fail%5C%22%3Eno%20independently-policed%20ethical%20code%20of%20conduct%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20cannot%20easily%20be%20removed%20from%20their%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPreviously%2C%20when%20Trump%20had%20asked%20the%20SC%20to%20rule%20on%20whether%20as%20president%20he%20was%20exempt%20from%20all%20laws%2C%20the%20SC%20decided%20it%20%3Cem%3Ewas%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20matter%20for%20the%20courts%20but%20sent%20the%20case%20to%20an%20appeals%20court.%20When%20the%20latter%20ruled%20against%20Trump%20in%20the%20starkest%20terms%2C%20the%20SC%20decided%20to%20take%20the%20case%20but%20not%20until%20the%20end%20of%20April%2C%20causing%20further%20delay%20in%20a%20key%20year.%20This%20delay%20virtually%20guarantees%20there%20will%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2Ff450d649-6449-4c2d-87fd-b608dfd9c500%5C%22%3Eno%20trials%20as%20such%20for%20months%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20the%20SC%E2%80%99s%20ruling%20may%20not%20be%20available%20until%20the%20summer.%C2%A0Trump%20may%20get%20what%20he%E2%80%99s%20wanted%20all%20along%3A%20to%20drag%20out%20proceedings%20until%20after%20the%20election%20which%2C%20should%20he%20win%2C%20he%20would%20undoubtedly%20dismiss%20as%20the%20workings%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98deep%20state%E2%80%99%20against%20a%20man%20of%20the%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20SC%20has%2C%20therefore%2C%20presented%20Trump%20and%20the%20GOP%20immunity%20from%20laws%20and%20constitutional%20norms.%20Those%20Trump-inspired%20insurrectionists%20of%20January%206%2C%202021%20are%20free%20to%20run%20for%20future%20office%20%E2%80%93%20and%20a%20large%20number%20of%20them%20have%20been%20sitting%20in%20the%20House%20and%20Senate%20since%20then%20in%20any%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Republican%20party%20%E2%80%93%20a%20full-fledged%20far%20right%20party%20%E2%80%93%20is%20now%20above%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20%E2%80%98Super%20Tuesday%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20the%20suspension%20by%20Nikki%20Haley%20of%20her%20campaign%2C%20Trump%20is%20guaranteed%20to%20win%20the%20Republican%20party%20nomination%20for%20the%20presidential%20election%20in%20November.%20More%2C%20he%20leads%20in%20several%20national%20opinion%20polls%20against%20his%20Democratic%20incumbent%2C%20President%20Joe%20Biden.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20in%20the%20position%20that%2C%20should%20Trump%20emerge%20victorious%20in%20November%2C%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20so-called%20free%20world%20faces%20the%20prospect%20of%20governing%20from%20prison%2C%20were%20the%20justice%20system%20to%20take%20its%20normal%20course.%20But%20there%20is%20nothing%20normal%20about%20our%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBiden%20administration%20on%20the%20ropes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJoseph%20Biden%20reportedly%20decided%20to%20come%20out%20of%20retirement%20and%20run%20against%20Trump%20in%202020%20after%20pro-Trump%20neo-Nazis%20and%20white%20supremacists%20rioted%20in%20Charlottesville%20in%202017%2C%20killing%20a%20counter-protestor.%20Biden%20wanted%20to%20fight%20for%20the%20%E2%80%98soul%E2%80%99%20of%20America%2C%20be%20its%20saviour%20in%20time%20of%20national%20need.%20Instead%2C%20he%20may%20well%20be%20the%20lead%20actor%20in%20a%20tragedy%20%E2%80%93%20the%20saviour%20who%20paves%20the%20way%20for%20Trump%20II%2C%20a%20newly-emboldened%20and%20revived%20leader%20swearing%20vengeance%20on%20his%20opponents%20and%20a%20dictatorship%20to%20boot.%20Close%20the%20borders%2C%20deport%20millions%20of%20immigrants%2C%20burn%20down%20regulation%20of%20oil%20and%20gas%2C%20free%20the%20corporations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERacist%20divide-and-rule%20coupled%20with%20complete%20freedom%20for%20corporations%2C%20whose%20executives%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2Ff450d649-6449-4c2d-87fd-b608dfd9c500%5C%22%3Econtinue%20to%20back%3C%2Fa%3E%20Trump%20and%20the%20far%20right%20GOP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBiden%20has%20coupled%20his%20disastrous%20appeasement%20of%20Trump%20and%20the%20GOP%20with%20an%20equally%20disastrous%20foreign%20policy.%20He%20now%20faces%20a%20political%20backlash%20related%20to%20his%20administration%E2%80%99s%20military%2C%20financial%20and%20diplomatic%20support%20for%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20horrific%20war%20on%20Gaza.%20Biden%20is%20alienating%2C%20according%20to%20reliable%20polls%2C%20two%20key%20constituencies%20that%20may%20render%20him%20a%20one-term%20president%3A%20Arab%20and%20Muslim%20Americans%2C%20and%20younger%20voters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20a%20tiny%20percentage%20of%20the%20US%20electorate%2C%20Muslim%20Americans%20could%20be%20the%20margin%20in%20key%20states%20that%20swings%20the%20election%20for%20Trump%2C%20even%20if%20they%20stay%20home.%20This%20is%20especially%20the%20case%20in%20states%20such%20as%20Michigan%20but%20also%20Georgia%20and%20Pennsylvania.%20Arab%20and%20Muslim%20American%20voters%20overwhelmingly%20supported%20Biden%20against%20the%20Islamophobic%20Trump%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYounger%20voters%2C%20a%20far%20larger%20section%20of%20the%20Democratic%20party%E2%80%99s%20voter%20base%2C%20are%20also%20vexed%20by%20Biden%E2%80%99s%20Israel-Gaza%20policies%20and%20opposition%20to%20a%20ceasefire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3EAmericans%E2%80%99%20choice%3A%20Anger%20vs%20fear%2C%20not%20democracy%20vs%20dictatorship%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20what%20does%20all%20this%20boil%20down%20to%20in%20this%20critical%20election%20year%3F%20What%20are%20the%20options%20for%20voters%3F%20In%20the%20end%2C%20it%20would%20appear%20that%20Americans%20must%20decide%20if%20their%20anger%20and%20frustrations%20with%20the%20Biden%20administration%20outweigh%20their%20fear%20of%20a%20Trump%20second%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20suspect%20that%20the%20Biden%20administration%20is%20(if%20increasingly%20anxiously)%20satisfied%20that%20Trump%20is%20their%20opponent%20for%20the%20White%20House.%20Indeed%2C%20that%20was%20always%20the%20plan.%20Fear%20of%20Trump%20may%20ultimately%2C%20in%20the%20privacy%20of%20the%20voting%20booth%2C%20drive%20voters%20into%20Democrats%E2%80%99%20arms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20fitting%20might%20that%20be%3A%20Trump%20who%20used%20fear%20so%20skilfully%20in%202016%20is%20the%20unwitting%20author%20of%20his%20own%20downfall.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Biden%E2%80%99s%20strategy%20of%20appeasement%20may%20well%20backfire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fiparmar%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EInderjeet%20Parmar%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20professor%20of%20international%20politics%20and%20associate%20dean%20of%20research%20in%20the%20School%20of%20Policy%20and%20Global%20Affairs%20at%20City%2C%20University%20of%20London%2C%20a%20fellow%20of%20the%20Academy%20of%20Social%20Sciences%2C%20and%20a%20columnist%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Wire%3Cem%3E.%20He%20is%20an%20International%20Fellow%20at%20the%20ROADS%20Initiative%20think%20tank%2C%20Islamabad%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3Eand%20author%20of%20several%20books%20including%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EFoundations%20of%20the%20American%20Century%3Cem%3E.%20He%20is%20currently%20writing%20a%20book%20on%20the%20history%2C%20politics%2C%20and%20powers%20of%20the%20US%20Foreign%20Policy%20Establishment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709885441000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F03124308%2F1080px-President_Trump_Travels_to_Arizona_50040937841.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Famerican-constitution-rip-us-spiralling-crises-accelerate-in-critical-election-year%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Americans%20must%20decide%20if%20their%20anger%20and%20frustrations%20with%20the%20Biden%20administration%20outweigh%20their%20fear%20of%20a%20Trump%20second%20term.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Famerican-constitution-rip-us-spiralling-crises-accelerate-in-critical-election-year%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Shastri%2C%20Manjrekar%20Rub%20Salt%20On%20Ben%2