Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20financial%20services%20worker%20in%20Shanghai%20who%20was%20fired%20for%20browsing%20pornographic%20websites%20at%20work%20has%20sued%20his%20former%20employer%2C%20blaming%20a%20virus%20that%20infected%20his%20computer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2041-year-old%20client%20relationship%20manager%2C%20identified%20by%20the%20municipal%20high%20court%20by%20his%20surname%20Yang%2C%20sought%20%2443%2C000%20in%20damages%20and%20said%20his%20contract%20was%20wrongfully%20terminated%2C%20authorities%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweibo.com%2Fttarticle%2Fp%2Fshow%3Fid%3D2309405009221782470997%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20a%20report%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChinese%20courts%20do%20not%20typically%20name%20prosecutors%20and%20defendants%20in%20full%20for%20civil%20cases%20that%20are%20not%20high-profile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYang%20had%20worked%20for%20five%20years%20under%20his%20employer%20and%20earned%20about%20%242%2C360%20a%20month%20until%20he%20was%20fired%20in%20August%202022%2C%20per%20the%20Shanghai%20High%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20average%20monthly%20salary%20in%20urban%20Shanghai%20was%20around%20%241%2C700%20that%20year%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.shpt.gov.cn%2Fshpt%2Ffy-fyzx%2F20230629%2F903363.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3D%25E6%259C%25AC%25E5%25B8%25822022%25E5%25B9%25B4%25E5%25BA%25A6%25E5%2585%25A8%2C%25E8%25B0%2583%25E6%2595%25B4%25E4%25B8%25BA7310%25E5%2585%2583%252F%25E6%259C%2588%25E3%2580%2582%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elatest%20government%20statistics.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYang's%20employer%20said%20that%20Yang%20had%20breached%20his%20contract%20%E2%80%94%20which%20prohibits%20employees%20from%20consuming%20pornography%20at%20work%20%E2%80%94%20by%20accessing%20%26quot%3Blittle%20movies%26quot%3B%20on%20his%20work%20computer.%20The%20term%20is%20a%20euphemism%20in%20China%20for%20explicit%20videos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Yang%20submitted%20company%20records%20that%20showed%20his%20colleagues%20often%20downloaded%20movies%20or%20shows%20on%20their%20work%20computers%20outside%20business%20hours.%20He%20said%20that%20this%20may%20have%20caused%20his%20computer%20to%20become%20infected%20by%20Trojan%20malware%2C%20per%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20showed%20the%20court%20a%20photo%20of%20his%20office%2C%20which%20was%20an%20open%20space%20with%20no%20speakers%2C%20and%20said%20such%20a%20working%20environment%20was%20not%20conducive%20for%20consuming%20pornographic%20material%2C%20the%20report%20said.%20Yang%20said%20the%20%26quot%3Blittle%20movies%26quot%3B%20thus%20must%20have%20been%20watched%20by%20someone%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EYang%20admitted%20to%20an%20adult%20site%20membership%20in%20his%20'personal%20reflection'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYang's%20employer%2C%20who%20was%20not%20named%2C%20fired%20back%20with%20internet%20records%20that%20showed%20the%20adult%20site%20browsing%20was%20performed%20while%20Yang%20sent%20files%20to%20colleagues%20and%20actively%20performed%20work%20tasks%2C%20indicating%20he%20was%20using%20the%20computer%20at%20the%20time%2C%20per%20the%20Shanghai%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20showed%20the%20court%20a%20transcript%20from%20a%20messaging%20chat%20group%2C%20where%20Yang%20wrote%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bpersonal%20reflection%26quot%3B%20submission%20to%20his%20boss%20that%20he%20had%20signed%20up%20for%20a%20membership%20on%20an%20adult%20content%20website%20and%20struggled%20with%20self-discipline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20reflection%2C%20Yang%20said%20he%20would%20have%20to%20repeatedly%20return%20to%20the%20website%20to%20click%20on%20links%2C%20allowing%20him%20to%20earn%20points%20and%20maintain%20his%20membership%20status%2C%20per%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22682%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20taken%20during%20Yang's%20hearing.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65eaaf7690413ab8e1da9d